1069_133699_000050_000000 "Thank you for doing so." And Isabel turned away.
1069_133699_000051_000000 "Yes, you're changed; you've got new ideas over here," her friend continued.
1069_133699_000052_000000 "I hope so," said Isabel; "one should get as many new ideas as possible."
1069_133699_000053_000000 "Yes; but they shouldn't interfere with the old ones when the old ones have been the right ones."
1069_133699_000054_000000 Isabel turned about again.
1069_133699_000054_000001 "If you mean that I had any idea with regard to mr Goodwood-!" But she faltered before her friend's implacable glitter.
1069_133699_000055_000000 "My dear child, you certainly encouraged him."
1069_133699_000056_000000 Isabel made for the moment as if to deny this charge; instead of which, however, she presently answered: "It's very true.
1069_133699_000056_000001 I did encourage him." And then she asked if her companion had learned from mr Goodwood what he intended to do.
1069_133699_000057_000000 "I asked him, and he said he meant to do nothing," Miss Stackpole answered.
1069_133699_000057_000001 "But I don't believe that; he's not a man to do nothing.
1069_133699_000057_000002 He is a man of high, bold action.
1069_133699_000058_000000 "I quite believe that." Henrietta might be wanting in delicacy, but it touched the girl, all the same, to hear this declaration.
1069_133699_000059_000000 "Ah, you do care for him!" her visitor rang out.
1069_133699_000060_000000 "Whatever he does will always be right," Isabel repeated.
1069_133699_000060_000001 "When a man's of that infallible mould what does it matter to him what one feels?"
1069_133699_000061_000000 "It may not matter to him, but it matters to one's self."
1069_133699_000062_000000 "Ah, what it matters to me-that's not what we're discussing," said Isabel with a cold smile.
1069_133699_000063_000000 This time her companion was grave.
1069_133699_000063_000001 "Well, I don't care; you have changed.
1069_133699_000063_000002 You're not the girl you were a few short weeks ago, and mr Goodwood will see it.
1069_133699_000063_000003 I expect him here any day."
1069_133699_000064_000000 "I hope he'll hate me then," said Isabel.
1069_133699_000065_000000 "I believe you hope it about as much as I believe him capable of it."
1069_133699_000066_000001 She pretended to herself, however, that she thought the event impossible, and, later, she communicated her disbelief to her friend.
1069_133699_000066_000003 The feeling pressed upon her; it made the air sultry, as if there were to be a change of weather; and the weather, socially speaking, had been so agreeable during Isabel's stay at Gardencourt that any change would be for the worse.
1069_133699_000066_000004 Her suspense indeed was dissipated the second day.
1069_133699_000066_000006 She entertained herself for some moments with talking to the little terrier, as to whom the proposal of an ownership divided with her cousin had been applied as impartially as possible-as impartially as Bunchie's own somewhat fickle and inconstant sympathies would allow.
1069_133699_000066_000007 But she was notified for the first time, on this occasion, of the finite character of Bunchie's intellect; hitherto she had been mainly struck with its extent.
1069_133699_000066_000008 It seemed to her at last that she would do well to take a book; formerly, when heavy hearted, she had been able, with the help of some well chosen volume, to transfer the seat of consciousness to the organ of pure reason.
1069_133699_000066_000009 Of late, it was not to be denied, literature had seemed a fading light, and even after she had reminded herself that her uncle's library was provided with a complete set of those authors which no gentleman's collection should be without, she sat motionless and empty handed, her eyes bent on the cool green turf of the lawn.
1069_133699_000066_000010 Her meditations were presently interrupted by the arrival of a servant who handed her a letter.
1069_133699_000066_000011 The letter bore the London postmark and was addressed in a hand she knew-that came into her vision, already so held by him, with the vividness of the writer's voice or his face.
1069_133699_000066_000012 This document proved short and may be given entire.
1069_133699_000067_000000 MY DEAR MISS ARCHER-I don't know whether you will have heard of my coming to England, but even if you have not it will scarcely be a surprise to you.
1069_133699_000067_000002 I protested against it. You in fact appeared to accept my protest and to admit that I had the right on my side.
1069_133699_000067_000003 I had come to see you with the hope that you would let me bring you over to my conviction; my reasons for entertaining this hope had been of the best.
1069_133699_000067_000005 You admitted that you were unreasonable, and it was the only concession you would make; but it was a very cheap one, because that's not your character.
1069_133699_000067_000006 No, you are not, and you never will be, arbitrary or capricious.
1069_133699_000067_000008 You told me that I'm not disagreeable to you, and I believe it; for I don't see why that should be.
1069_133699_000067_000010 If I like this country at present it is only because it holds you.
1069_133699_000067_000011 I have been to England before, but have never enjoyed it much.
1069_133699_000067_000013 This at present is the dearest wish of yours faithfully,
1069_133699_000068_000000 CASPAR GOODWOOD.
1069_133699_000069_000001 Looking up, however, as she mechanically folded it she saw Lord Warburton standing before her.
1069_133709_000043_000029 This was not, as it may seem, merely a theory tinged with sarcasm.
1069_133709_000043_000030 Isabel candidly believed that his lordship would, in the usual phrase, get over his disappointment.
1069_133709_000043_000031 He had been deeply affected-this she believed, and she was still capable of deriving pleasure from the belief; but it was absurd that a man both so intelligent and so honourably dealt with should cultivate a scar out of proportion to any wound.
1069_133709_000043_000033 It would have proved that he believed she was firm-which was what she wished to seem to him.
