1088_134315_000013_000000 "I have heard of him," said the girl.
1088_134315_000014_000000 "A man with a singular mind," said Kara; "a man against whom my favourite weapon would fail."
1088_134315_000015_000000 She looked at him with interest in her eyes.
1088_134315_000016_000000 "What is your favourite weapon, mr Kara?" she asked.
1088_134315_000018_000001 Probably he required no such encouragement, for in the presence of his social inferiors he was somewhat monopolizing.
1088_134315_000019_000000 "Cut a man's flesh and it heals," he said.
1088_134315_000019_000002 Fear is a tyrant and a despot, more terrible than the rack, more potent than the stake.
1088_134315_000020_000000 "Is that your creed?" she asked quietly.
1088_134315_000021_000000 "Part of it, Miss Holland," he smiled.
1088_134315_000022_000000 She played idly with the letter she held in her hand, balancing it on the edge of the desk, her eyes downcast.
1088_134315_000023_000000 "What would justify the use of such an awful weapon?" she asked.
1088_134315_000024_000000 "It is amply justified to secure an end," he said blandly.
1088_134315_000024_000001 "For example-I want something-I cannot obtain that something through the ordinary channel or by the employment of ordinary means.
1088_134315_000024_000003 If I can buy it, well and good.
1088_134315_000024_000004 If I can buy those who can use their influence to secure this thing for me, so much the better.
1088_134315_000024_000005 If I can obtain it by any merit I possess, I utilize that merit, providing always, that I can secure my object in the time, otherwise-"
1088_134315_000025_000000 He shrugged his shoulders.
1088_134315_000026_000000 "I see," she said, nodding her head quickly.
1088_134315_000026_000001 "I suppose that is how blackmailers feel."
