1098_133695_000013_000009 It's very pleasant to be so well treated where one had least looked for it.
1098_133695_000013_000010 I had never been more blue, more bored, than for a week before she came; I had never expected less that anything pleasant would happen.
1098_133695_000013_000012 The key of a beautiful edifice is thrust into my hand, and I'm told to walk in and admire.
1098_133695_000013_000018 She was intelligent and generous; it was a fine free nature; but what was she going to do with herself?
1098_133695_000013_000019 This question was irregular, for with most women one had no occasion to ask it.
1098_133695_000013_000020 Most women did with themselves nothing at all; they waited, in attitudes more or less gracefully passive, for a man to come that way and furnish them with a destiny.
1098_133695_000013_000021 Isabel's originality was that she gave one an impression of having intentions of her own.
1098_133695_000013_000022 "Whenever she executes them," said Ralph, "may I be there to see!"
1098_133695_000014_000000 It devolved upon him of course to do the honours of the place.
1098_133695_000014_000001 mr Touchett was confined to his chair, and his wife's position was that of rather a grim visitor; so that in the line of conduct that opened itself to Ralph duty and inclination were harmoniously mixed.
