1263_139804_000001_000000 CHAPTER twenty.
1263_139804_000003_000002 They are nearly as large as we and relatively much lighter in weight.
1263_139804_000003_000003 All the periods of physical growth are correspondingly decreased.
1263_139804_000003_000004 Children walk four or five weeks after birth, and are capable of receiving regular instruction at the age of five months.
1263_139804_000004_000000 Strange as it may seem, this sphere, which for convenience we will call Brief, revolves very slowly on its axis, so that our world makes fifteen times as many revolutions as this planet.
1263_139804_000005_000004 It appears that on all worlds everything is regulated in accordance with the length of human life.
1263_139804_000005_000005 On this world, of Brief all vegetables mature in periods so short that one marvels when he hears it.
1263_139804_000005_000006 Think of cereals reaching maturity in seven or eight of our days, or during one day of Brief.
1263_139804_000005_000007 Early in the morning certain crops are planted and are harvested at night.
1263_139804_000006_000000 If you were permitted to look upon the public and private life of this incredible world, your first sensation would be dizziness, not to mention the weirdness of all sights that would confront you at every turn.
1263_139804_000007_000000 Furrows of care and trouble begin to deepen on the faces of these Briefites as they approach an age of what we would call three years, and if by lease of strength they pass on toward an age of four years, it is but an evidence of their exceptional vitality.
1263_139804_000009_000000 JOURNALISM.
1263_139804_000010_000000 Things happen in such quick succession that the news is hustled out at all hours of the day and night; not on sheets of paper, but through automatic news receivers, machines somewhat akin to our telegraph instruments.
1263_139804_000011_000003 But compared to our customs, the news is very scarce.
1263_139804_000011_000004 There being no competition, no time or space is required for sensational trash.
1263_139804_000011_000005 Thus, if nothing of importance occurs, nothing need be transmitted.
1263_139804_000011_000008 The government verifies, as much as possible, all reports before they are transmitted.
1263_139804_000011_000009 There are indeed some advantages in the government being in constant touch with each home under its care. The advertising department pays nearly all expenses of this whole system of journalism.
1263_139804_000011_000010 Announcements for private gain are paid at a regular rate.
1263_139804_000011_000011 It costs more to advertise at certain periods than at other times, all regulated by the customs of the people.
1263_139804_000012_000001 Of course, people take their choice as to reading advertisements.
1263_139804_000014_000000 THEIR FOOTWEAR.
1263_139804_000015_000001 They never think of covering the feet under any change of climate.
1263_139804_000015_000002 If one of the Briefites were to step upon the shores of our rugged Earth and see the cotton or wool and leather that lies around our feet, it would appear to him as the most ridiculous thing imaginable, and no doubt his shapely feet of ivory cast would be of more than passing interest to us.
1263_139804_000016_000000 THEIR RAIMENT.
1263_139804_000017_000000 Their raiment is altogether after new models.
1263_139804_000017_000003 Their garments partake of the loose flowing order.
1263_139804_000017_000004 For instance, a strong fabric of chosen shade is fastened at the neck, hip, knee and ankle, and lies carelessly over the parts between.
1263_139804_000017_000005 The females never graduated to the corset degree, and while they do not cut a scientific figure, yet they surely develop a more ruddy waist after the model intended by the Designor of the body.
1263_139804_000019_000003 In a city of Brief, overhead tracks after such an order run along all business streets and certain residence streets.
1263_139804_000019_000004 Spare me a detailed description of this peculiar traveling system.
1263_139804_000019_000005 Suffice it to say that a person, in lightning rapidity of motion, rushes from a store, springs upon a passing seat and is hurled away by the power of an overhead cable system.
1263_139804_000020_000003 I have no words of praise for this system, although the Briefites can cover considerable territory in an hour.
1263_139804_000020_000004 They look upon this gravity system as a wonderful achievement, for it has not been in operation for more than three hundred years.
1263_139804_000021_000000 The power of steam has never been utilized.
1263_139804_000021_000002 But they have discovered what we would call gaseous oil, and have learned to put it to work, so that it is the main force employed in hoisting and all other purposes where power is required.
1263_139804_000022_000000 Nothing like a traveling locomotive has ever been made, although I learned that a bright wizard was experimenting and that he prophesied great changes when his gas propelled vehicle was perfected.
1263_139804_000023_000001 Quadrupeds that take the place of our horses are used for drayage, although nothing except the two wheeled class of vehicles was ever used until some eighty seven years ago.
1263_139804_000027_000001 They are much purer in morals, more refined in manner, more harmonious in government, and unusually bright in mathematics.
1263_139804_000027_000005 This is principally due to their lack of time.
1263_139804_000028_000000 RELIGIOUS LIFE.
1263_139804_000029_000000 The religious life of the people of Brief is, on an average, of a higher type than is found in our world.
1263_139804_000030_000000 Their Redeemer is worshiped quite separately from God, and with distinctive adorations.
1263_139804_000030_000001 The name of their Redeemer, phonetically rendered, is Kerm Cher.
1263_139804_000030_000002 The most faithful translation of this word into our language would be God affluence.
1263_139804_000031_000001 Similar to Christ, he confirmed his identity by unanswerable miracles.
1263_139804_000032_000000 Many, however, disbelieved in Kerm Cher, and held to the old axiomatic truths.
1263_139804_000032_000001 Thus creeds were prevalent and they remain until now, only there is much less variety than is found amongst us.
