1263_141777_000017_000005 Was the other out to spy on them?
1263_141777_000017_000006 That idea made sense.
1263_141777_000017_000007 And in the meantime he would let the other past him, follow along behind until he was far enough from the camp so that his friends could not interfere-then, they would have a meeting!
1263_141777_000018_000000 Rynch's fingers balled into fists.
1263_141777_000018_000002 That other would know, and would tell him the truth!
1263_141777_000019_000000 Alert as he was, he lost sight of the stranger who melted into the dusky cover of the shadows.
1263_141777_000019_000002 The man from the spacer camp was using the stream as his road.
1263_141777_000020_000000 In spite of his caution Rynch was close to betrayal as he edged around a clump of vegetation growing half in, half out of the stream.
1263_141777_000020_000001 Only a timely rustle told him that the other had sat down on a drift log.
1263_141777_000021_000000 Waiting for him?
1263_141777_000021_000001 Rynch froze, so startled that he could not think clearly for a second.
1263_141777_000021_000002 Then he noted that the outline of the other's body was visible, growing brighter by the moment.
1263_141777_000022_000001 The dark shadow of an arm flapped, the radiance swirled, broke again into pinpoint sparks.
1263_141777_000023_000001 He pushed back into the bushes while the sparks still flitted, but they no longer gathered in strength enough to light his presence.
1263_141777_000023_000002 Now he could see they drifted about the vegetation, about the log where the man sat, about rocks and reeds.
1263_141777_000023_000004 He continued to keep them whirling by means of waving hand and arm, but there was enough light to show Rynch the fingers of his other hand, busy on the front panel of the box he wore.
1263_141777_000024_000000 That fingering stopped, then Rynch's head came up as he heard a very faint sound.
1263_141777_000024_000001 Not a beast's cry-or was it?
1263_141777_000025_000000 Again those fingers moved on the panel.
1263_141777_000025_000001 Was the other sending a message by that means?
1263_141777_000025_000002 Rynch watched him check the webbing, count the equipment at his belt, settle the needler in the crook of his arm. Then the stranger left the stream, headed towards the woods.
1263_141777_000026_000000 Rynch jumped to his feet, a cry of warning shaping, but not to be uttered.
1263_141777_000026_000001 He padded after the other.
1263_141777_000026_000002 There was plenty of time to stop the man before he reached the danger which might lurk under the trees.
1263_141777_000027_000000 However the other was as wary of that dark as if he suspected what might lie in wait there.
1263_141777_000029_000000 Thankfully Rynch found his own lurking place from which he could keep the other in sight.
1263_141777_000029_000001 The light points gathered, hung in a small luminous cloud over the rocks.
1263_141777_000029_000002 But Rynch had prudently withdrawn under a bush, and the scent of its aromatic leaves must have discouraged the sparks, for no such crown came to his sentry post.
1263_141777_000030_000001 To open his eyes to this blue green pocket instead of to four dirty walls, was wrong.
1263_141777_000031_000000 Remembering, he started up and slunk down the slope, angry at his failure.
1263_141777_000031_000001 He found the other's track, not turning back as he had half feared, cleanly printed on level spots of wet earth-eastward now. What was the purpose of the other's expedition?
1263_141777_000032_000001 The man from the spacer had made no effort to conceal his trail, in fact it would almost seem that he had deliberately gone out of his way to leave boot prints on favorable stretches of ground.
1263_141777_000032_000002 Did he guess that Rynch lurked behind, was now leading him on for some purpose of his own?
1263_141777_000032_000003 Or were those traces left to guide another party from the camp?
1263_141777_000033_000000 To advance openly up the stream bed was to invite discovery.
1263_141777_000033_000001 Rynch surveyed the nearer bank.
1263_141777_000033_000002 Clumps of small trees and high growing bushes dotted that expanse, an ideal cover.
1263_141777_000034_000001 And the feline was attacking an enemy, enraged to the pitch of vocal frenzy.
1263_141777_000034_000002 Rynch ran a zigzag course from one clump of bush to the next.
1263_141777_000034_000003 That sound of snarling, spitting hate ended in mid cry as Rynch crawled to the river bank.
1263_141777_000035_000000 The man from the spacer camp had been the focus of a three prong attack from a female and her cubs.
1263_141777_000035_000001 Three red bodies were flat and still on the gravel as the off worlder leaned back against a rock breathing heavily.
1263_141777_000035_000002 As Rynch sighted him, he stooped to recover the needler he had dropped, lurched away from the rock towards the water, and so blundered straight into another Jumalan trap.
1263_141777_000036_000000 His unsteady foot advancing for another step came down on a slippery surface, and he fell forward as his legs were engulfed in the trap burrow of a strong jaws.
1263_141777_000036_000001 With a startled cry the man dropped the needler again, clawed at the ground about him.
1263_141777_000036_000003 But he had not lost his head and was jerking from side to side in an effort to pull free.
1263_141777_000037_000000 Rynch got to his feet, walked with slow deliberation down to the river's brink.
1263_141777_000037_000001 The trapped prisoner had shied halfway around, stretching out his arms to find a firmer grip on some rock large and heavy enough to anchor him.
1263_141777_000037_000002 After his first startled cry he had made no sound, but now, as he sighted Rynch, his eyes widened and his lips parted.
1263_141777_000038_000000 The box on his chest caught on a stone he had dragged to him in a desperate try for support.
1263_141777_000038_000001 There was a spitting of sparks and the stranger worked frantically at the buckle of the webbing harness to loosen it and toss the whole thing from him.
1263_141777_000038_000002 The box struck one of the dead water cats, flashed as fur and flesh were singed.
1263_141777_000039_000001 The man eyed him steadily, and his expression did not alter even when Rynch swung the off world weapon to center its sights on the late owner.
1263_141777_000040_000000 "Suppose," Rynch's voice was rusty sounding in his own ears, "we talk now."
1263_141777_000041_000000 The man nodded.
1263_141777_000041_000001 "As you wish, Brodie."
1334_135589_000001_000001 On his arrival at Paris, he was kindly received by King Charles, who promised to assist his views in joining the army.
1334_135589_000002_000000 "You have to choose between two generals, both great in the art of war-Conde and Turenne.
