1334_135589_000016_000002 Turenne bore down Conde, who had gained every campaign; and the court of Spain, wearied with reverses, made overtures of peace, which was gladly accepted by the French.
1334_135589_000018_000000 Edward, who but rarely heard from Humphrey, was now anxious to quit the army and go to the king, who was in Spain; but to leave his colors, while things were adverse, was impossible.
1334_135589_000019_000000 After the peace and the pardon of Conde by the French king, the armies were disbanded, and the three adventurers were free.
