1334_135589_000091_000000 About a year after the Restoration, there was a fete at Hampton Court, given in honor of three marriages taking place-Edward Beverley to Patience Heatherstone, Chaloner to Alice, and Grenville to Edith; and, as his majesty himself said, as he gave away the brides, "Could loyalty be better rewarded?"
1334_135589_000092_000000 But our young readers will not be content if they do not hear some particulars about the other personages who have appeared in our little history.
