1970_26100_000007_000000 THE ANSWER
1970_26100_000008_000000 The coroner and I drove out to the bridge that afternoon and I must admit I was mighty poor company.
1970_26100_000008_000001 Mary's unreasonableness, her stupid obstinacy, when she knew she was wrong and I was right, her willingness to break our friendship at the first opportunity, gave me little room to think of anything else.
