2836_5354_000026_000000 "Tush!" was the response of Captain Levison, as if wishing to imply that the divorce was yet a far off affair, and he proceeded to open the other letter.
2836_5354_000027_000000 "Sir-After sending off our last, dated to day, we received tidings of the demise of Sir peter Levison, your grand uncle.
2836_5354_000027_000001 He expired this afternoon in town, where he had come for the benefit of medical advice.
2836_5354_000027_000002 We have much pleasure in congratulating you upon your accession to the title and estates, and beg to state that should it not be convenient to you to visit England at present, we will be happy to transact all necessary matters for you, on your favoring us with instructions.
2836_5354_000027_000003 And we remain, sir, most faithfully yours,
2836_5354_000028_000000 "MOSS and GRAB.
2836_5354_000029_000000 "SIR FRANCIS LEVISON, Bart."
2836_5354_000030_000000 The outside of the letter was superscribed as the other, "F.
2836_5354_000031_000000 "At last, thank the pigs!" was the gentleman's euphonious expression, as he tossed the letter, open, on the breakfast table.
2836_5354_000032_000000 "The divorce is granted!" feverishly uttered Lady Isabel.
2836_5354_000033_000000 He made no reply, but seated himself to breakfast.
2836_5354_000034_000000 "May I read the letter?
2836_5354_000034_000001 Is it for me to read?"
2836_5354_000035_000000 "For what else should I have thrown it there?" he said.
2836_5354_000036_000000 "A few days ago you put a letter, open on the table, I thought for me; but when I took it up you swore at me.
2836_5354_000036_000001 Do you remember it Captain Levison?"
2836_5354_000037_000000 "You may drop that odious title, Isabel, which has stuck to me too long.
2836_5354_000037_000001 I own a better, now."
2836_5354_000038_000000 "What one, pray?"
2836_5354_000039_000000 "You can look and see."
2836_5354_000040_000001 Sir Francis swallowed down his coffee, and rang the table hand bell-the only bell you generally meet with in France.
2836_5354_000041_000001 "I start for England in an hour."
2836_5354_000042_000000 "It is very well," Pierre responded; and departed to do it.
2836_5354_000042_000001 Lady Isabel waited till the man was gone, and then spoke, a faint flush of emotion in her cheeks.
2836_5354_000043_000000 "You do not mean what you say?
2836_5354_000043_000001 You will not leave me yet?"
2836_5354_000044_000000 "I cannot do otherwise," he answered.
2836_5354_000045_000000 "Moss and Grab say they will act for you.
2836_5354_000045_000001 Had there been a necessity for your going, they would not have offered that."
2836_5354_000046_000001 Besides, I should not choose for the old man's funeral to take place without me."
2836_5354_000047_000000 "Then I must accompany you," she urged.
2836_5354_000048_000000 "I wish you would not talk nonsense, Isabel.
2836_5354_000048_000001 Are you in a state to travel night and day?
2836_5354_000048_000002 Neither would home be agreeable to you yet awhile."
2836_5354_000049_000000 She felt the force of the objections.
2836_5354_000049_000001 Resuming after a moment's pause- "Were you to go to England, you might not be back in time."
2836_5354_000051_000000 "Oh, how can you ask?" she rejoined, in a sharp tone of reproach; "you know too well.
2836_5354_000051_000001 In time to make me your wife when the divorce shall appear."
2836_5354_000053_000000 "Chance it! chance the legitimacy of the child?
2836_5354_000053_000001 You must assure that, before all things.
2836_5354_000054_000000 "Now don't put yourself in a fever, Isabel.
2836_5354_000054_000001 How many times am I to be compelled to beg that of you!
2836_5354_000054_000002 It does no good.
2836_5354_000054_000003 Is it my fault, if I am called suddenly to England?"
2836_5354_000055_000000 "Have you no pity for your child?" she urged in agitation.
2836_5354_000055_000001 "Nothing can repair the injury, if you once suffer it to come upon him.
2836_5354_000055_000002 He will be a by word amidst men throughout his life."
