2836_5354_000066_000000 "No, not yet.
2836_5354_000067_000000 "I cannot wait," he replied, his tone changing to one of determination.
2836_5354_000068_000000 He broke from her and left the room, and in another minute had left the house, Pierre attending him.
2836_5354_000068_000001 A feeling, amounting to a conviction, rushed over the unhappy lady that she had seen him for the last time until it was too late.
2836_5354_000069_000000 She was right.
2836_5354_000069_000001 It was too late by weeks and months.
2836_5354_000070_000000 December came in.
2836_5354_000070_000001 The Alps were covered with snow; Grenoble borrowed the shade, and looked cold, and white, and sleety, and sloppy; the gutters, running through the middle of certain of the streets, were unusually black, and the people crept along especially dismal.
2836_5354_000070_000003 She had an invalid cap on, and a thick woolen invalid shawl, and she shook and shivered perpetually; though she had drawn so close to the wood fire that there was a danger of her petticoats igniting, and the attendant had frequently to spring up and interpose between them and the crackling logs.
2836_5354_000070_000004 Little did it seem to matter to Lady Isabel; she sat in one position, her countenance the picture of stony despair.
2836_5354_000071_000002 She had got so far about as to sit up in the windy chamber; and it seemed to be to her a matter of perfect indifference whether she ever got out of it.
2836_5354_000072_000000 This day she had partaken of her early dinner-such as it was, for her appetite failed-and had dozed asleep in the arm chair, when a noise arose from below, like a carriage driving into the courtyard through the porte cochere.
2836_5354_000072_000001 It instantly aroused her.
2836_5354_000072_000002 Had he come?
2836_5354_000073_000000 "Who is it?" she asked of the nurse.
2836_5354_000075_000001 Another moment, and it was flung open.
2836_5354_000076_000000 Sir Francis Levison approached to greet her as he came in.
2836_5354_000076_000001 She waved him off, begging him, in a subdued, quiet tone, not to draw too near, as any little excitement made her faint now.
2836_5354_000076_000002 He took a seat opposite to her, and began pushing the logs together with his boot, as he explained that he really could not get away from town before.
2836_5354_000077_000000 "Why did you come now?" she quietly rejoined.
2836_5354_000078_000000 "Why did I come?" repeated he.
2836_5354_000078_000001 "Are these all the thanks a fellow gets for travelling in this inclement weather?
2836_5355_000007_000002 I wish to deal with you quite unreservedly, without concealment, or deceit; I must request you so to deal with me."
2836_5355_000008_000000 "What do you mean by 'deal?'" he asked, settling the logs to his apparent satisfaction.
2836_5355_000009_000000 "To speak and act.
2836_5355_000009_000001 Let there be plain truth between us at this interview, if there never has been before."
2836_5355_000010_000000 "I don't understand you."
