2952_410_000029_000000 With the head still hanging to his sleeve he went back to the house, and there caught sight of the other four Rokuro Kubi squatting together, with their bruised and bleeding heads reunited to their bodies.
2952_410_000029_000001 But when they perceived him at the back door all screamed, "The priest! the priest!"--and fled, through the other doorway, out into the woods.
2952_410_000030_000000 Eastward the sky was brightening; day was about to dawn; and Kwairyo knew that the power of the goblins was limited to the hours of darkness.
2952_410_000030_000003 After which he gathered together his few belongings, and leisurely descended the mountain to continue his journey.
2952_410_000031_000003 As the Kwairyo, he only smiled and said nothing when they questioned him.
2952_410_000031_000004 So, after having passed a night in prison, he was brought before the magistrates of the district.
2952_410_000031_000005 Then he was ordered to explain how he, a priest, had been found with the head of a man fastened to his sleeve, and why he had dared thus shamelessly to parade his crime in the sight of people.
2952_410_000033_000000 "Sirs, I did not fasten the head to my sleeve: it fastened itself there-much against my will.
2952_410_000033_000001 And I have not committed any crime.
2952_410_000033_000003 And he proceeded to relate the whole of the adventure,--bursting into another hearty laugh as he told of his encounter with the five heads.
2952_410_000034_000001 They judged him to be a hardened criminal, and his story an insult to their intelligence.
2952_410_000034_000002 Therefore, without further questioning, they decided to order his immediate execution,--all of them except one, a very old man.
2952_410_000034_000003 This aged officer had made no remark during the trial; but, after having heard the opinion of his colleagues, he rose up, and said:--
2952_410_000035_000000 "Let us first examine the head carefully; for this, I think, has not yet been done.
2952_410_000035_000001 If the priest has spoken truth, the head itself should bear witness for him...
2952_410_000035_000002 Bring the head here!"
2952_410_000036_000000 So the head, still holding in its teeth the koromo that had been stripped from Kwairyo's shoulders, was put before the judges.
2952_410_000036_000001 The old man turned it round and round, carefully examined it, and discovered, on the nape of its neck, several strange red characters.
2952_410_000036_000002 He called the attention of his colleagues to these, and also bade them observe that the edges of the neck nowhere presented the appearance of having been cut by any weapon.
2952_410_000036_000003 On the contrary, the line of leverance was smooth as the line at which a falling leaf detaches itself from the stem...
2952_410_000036_000004 Then said the elder:--
2952_410_000037_000000 "I am quite sure that the priest told us nothing but the truth.
2952_410_000037_000001 This is the head of a Rokuro Kubi.
2952_410_000037_000002 In the book Nan ho i butsu shi it is written that certain red characters can always be found upon the nape of the neck of a real Rokuro Kubi.
2952_410_000037_000003 There are the characters: you can see for yourselves that they have not been painted.
2952_410_000037_000004 Moreover, it is well known that such goblins have been dwelling in the mountains of the province of Kai from very ancient time...
2952_410_000037_000007 Perhaps you once belonged to the samurai class?"
2952_410_000038_000000 "You have guessed rightly, Sir," Kwairyo responded.
2952_410_000039_000000 At the mention of that name, a murmur of admiration filled the court room; for there were many present who remembered it.
2952_410_000039_000001 And Kwairyo immediately found himself among friends instead of judges,--friends anxious to prove their admiration by fraternal kindness.
2952_410_000039_000003 When Kwairyo left Suwa, he was as happy as any priest is permitted to be in this transitory world.
2952_410_000040_000000 And now it only remains to tell what became of the head.
2952_410_000041_000000 A day or two after leaving Suwa, Kwairyo met with a robber, who stopped him in a lonesome place, and bade him strip.
2952_410_000041_000001 Kwairyo at once removed his koromo, and offered it to the robber, who then first perceived what was hanging to the sleeve.
2952_410_000041_000002 Though brave, the highwayman was startled: he dropped the garment, and sprang back.
2952_410_000041_000006 Well, Sir priest, I suppose we are of the same calling; and I must say that I admire you!...
2952_410_000041_000008 Will you sell it?
2952_410_000041_000009 You can have my robe in exchange for your koromo; and I will give you five ryo for the head."
2952_410_000042_000000 Kwairyo answered:--
2952_410_000043_000000 "I shall let you have the head and the robe if you insist; but I must tell you that this is not the head of a man.
2952_410_000043_000001 It is a goblin's head.
