302_123516_000009_000001 He was a huge fellow, terribly scarred about the face and chest, and with one broken tusk and a missing ear.
302_123516_000009_000002 Strapped on either breast were human skulls and depending from these a number of dried human hands.
302_123516_000010_000000 His reference to the great games of which I had heard so much while among the Tharks convinced me that I had but jumped from purgatory into gehenna.
302_123516_000011_000000 After a few more words with the female, during which she assured him that I was now fully fit to travel, the jed ordered that we mount and ride after the main column.
302_123516_000012_000000 I was strapped securely to as wild and unmanageable a thoat as I had ever seen, and, with a mounted warrior on either side to prevent the beast from bolting, we rode forth at a furious pace in pursuit of the column.
302_123516_000013_000000 Just before dark we reached the main body of troops shortly after they had made camp for the night.
302_123516_000014_000000 Like the jed who had brought me, he was frightfully scarred, and also decorated with the breastplate of human skulls and dried dead hands which seemed to mark all the greater warriors among the Warhoons, as well as to indicate their awful ferocity, which greatly transcends even that of the Tharks.
302_123516_000015_000000 The jeddak, Bar Comas, who was comparatively young, was the object of the fierce and jealous hatred of his old lieutenant, Dak Kova, the jed who had captured me, and I could not but note the almost studied efforts which the latter made to affront his superior.
