311_124404_000002_000001 It was my design to comprise in it all that, before I set myself to write it, I thought I knew of the nature of material objects.
311_124404_000002_000008 To this I likewise added much respecting the substance, the situation, the motions, and all the different qualities of these heavens and stars; so that I thought I had said enough respecting them to show that there is nothing observable in the heavens or stars of our system that must not, or at least may not appear precisely alike in those of the system which I described.
311_124404_000002_000010 I was not, however, disposed, from these circumstances, to conclude that this world had been created in the manner I described; for it is much more likely that God made it at the first such as it was to be.
