3486_166446_000063_000000 "But in those caverns, under countless orbs of many colored lights"--again the thrill of amaze shook me-"they grew.
3486_166446_000063_000002 They burst into it-into yellow, glowing sunlight.
3486_166446_000063_000005 And that picture passed."
3486_166446_000064_000000 His voice deepened.
3486_166446_000065_000001 I saw our Earth-I knew, Goodwin, indisputably, unmistakably that it was our earth.
3486_166446_000065_000002 But its rolling hills were leveled, its mountains were ground and shaped into cold and polished symbols-geometric, fashioned.
3486_166446_000066_000001 The very Polar ice was chiseled.
3486_166446_000066_000002 On the ordered plains were traced the hieroglyphs of the faceted world.
3486_166446_000066_000003 And on all Earth, Goodwin, there was no green life, no city, no trace of man. On this Earth that had been ours were only-These.
3486_166446_000067_000001 "Don't think that I accept them in their entirety. Part truth, part illusion-the groping mind dazzled with light of unfamiliar truths and making pictures from half light and half shadow to help it understand.
3486_166446_000068_000000 "But still-SOME truth in them.
3486_166446_000068_000002 But this I do know-that last vision was of a cataclysm whose beginnings we face now-this very instant."
3486_166446_000070_000000 And suddenly I saw that mount as Earth-the city as Earth's cities-its gardens and groves as Earth's fields and forests-and the vanished people of Cherkis seemed to expand into all humanity.
3486_166446_000071_000000 "But Martin," I stammered, fighting against choking, intolerable terror, "there was something else.
3486_166446_000071_000002 A hope-a PROMISE, that they would NOT conquer."
3486_166446_000072_000000 "I remember," he replied, "but not clearly.
3486_166446_000072_000001 There WAS something-a shadow upon them, a menace.
3486_166446_000072_000002 It was a shadow that seemed to be born of our own world-some threatening spirit of earth hovering over them.
3486_166446_000073_000000 "I cannot remember; it eludes me.
3486_166446_000073_000001 Yet it is because I remember but a little of it that I say those drums may not be-taps-for us."
3486_166446_000074_000000 As though his words had been a cue, the sounds again burst forth-no longer muffled nor faint.
3486_166446_000075_000000 The drumming did not die; it grew louder, more vehement; defiant and deafening.
3486_166446_000075_000001 Within the Thing under us a mighty pulse began to throb, accelerating rapidly to the rhythm of that clamorous roll.
3486_166446_000076_000000 I saw Norhala draw herself up, sharply; stand listening and alert.
3486_166446_000076_000001 Under me, the throbbing turned to an uneasy churning, a ferment.
3486_166446_000077_000000 "Drums?" muttered Drake.
3486_166446_000077_000002 It's drum fire.
3486_166446_000077_000004 But where could batteries like those come from?"
3486_166446_000078_000000 "Drums," whispered Ventnor.
3486_166446_000078_000001 "They ARE drums.
3486_166446_000078_000002 The drums of Destiny!"
3486_166446_000079_000000 Louder the roaring grew.
3486_166446_000079_000001 Now it was a tremendous rhythmic cannonading. The Thing halted.
3486_166446_000079_000002 The tower that upheld ruth and Norhala swayed, bent over the gap between us, touched the top on which we rode.
3486_166446_000080_000000 Gently the two were plucked up; swiftly they were set beside us.
3486_166446_000081_000000 Came a shrill, keen wailing-louder than ever I had heard before.
3486_166446_000081_000001 There was an earthquake trembling; a maelstrom swirling in which we spun; a swift sinking.
3486_166446_000082_000000 The Thing split in two.
3486_166446_000082_000002 Into it streamed, over it clicked, score upon score of cubes, building it higher and higher.
3486_166446_000082_000003 It lurched forward-away from us.
