4160_11550_000043_000001 She was beginning to feel more strangely concerning mr Denis Oglethorpe, and it was Priscilla Gower who had stirred her heart.
4160_11550_000043_000002 She found Lady Throckmorton waiting at home for her, to her surprise, in a new mood.
4160_11550_000043_000003 She had that evening received a letter from Denis herself, and it had suggested an idea to her.
4160_11550_000044_000000 "I have been thinking, Theo," she said, "that we might take a run over the Channel ourselves.
4160_11550_000044_000002 The last time I visited the Spas, my health improved greatly."
4160_11550_000045_000001 She was a woman of caprices, and her caprices always ruled the day, as this one did, to Theo's great astonishment.
4160_11550_000045_000004 So when Theo broke into exclamations of pleasure and astonishment, she did not understand either her enthusiasm or her surprise.
4160_11550_000046_000001 Well, I think I have made up my mind about it.
4160_11550_000047_000001 She gave vent to no further exclamations. She would almost have been willing to give up the pleasure of the journey after that.
4160_11550_000047_000002 She was learning that it was best for her not to see Denis Oglethorpe again, and here it seemed that she must see him in spite of herself, even though she was conscientious enough to wish to do what was best, not so much because it was best for herself, as because it was just to Priscilla Gower.
4160_11550_000047_000004 She even wrote to Vienna, and told Denis that they were coming, herself and Theodora North, and he must wait and meet them if possible.
4160_11550_000048_000000 It was a great trial to Theodora, this.
