4267_287369_000005_000000 Gathered about the young inventor, the three men looked at the warning. The writing was poor, and it was evident that an attempt had been made to disguise it.
4267_287369_000005_000002 In fact, it was a very business like sort of warning.
4267_287369_000006_000000 "Rather odd," commented mr Jenks.
4267_287369_000006_000001 "Black paper and white ink."
4267_287369_000007_000000 "White ink is easy enough to make," stated mr Parker.
4267_287369_000007_000001 "I fancy they wanted it as conspicuous as possible."
4267_287369_000008_000000 "Yes," agreed Tom, "and this warning, together with the antics of the thing in white last night, shows that they are aware of our presence here, and perhaps know who we are.
4267_287369_000008_000001 We will have to be on our guard."
4267_287369_000009_000000 "Do you think that fellow Munson, whom we left in the forest, could have gotten here and warned them?" asked mr Damon.
4267_287369_000010_000000 "It's possible," admitted Tom, "but now let's see if the person who pinned this warning on our tent took any of our things."
4267_287369_000012_000000 "Well, we haven't had a great deal of success-so far," admitted Tom, as they sat about the fire, in the fast gathering dusk.
4267_287369_000012_000001 "I think, perhaps, we'd better try on the other side of the mountain to morrow.
4267_287369_000013_000000 "Good idea," commented mr Jenks.
4267_287369_000013_000001 "We'll do it, and move our camp.
4267_287369_000013_000002 I only hope those fellows don't find our airship and destroy it.
4267_287369_000014_000000 This contingency caused Tom some uneasiness.
4267_287369_000014_000001 He did not like to think that the unscrupulous men might damage the Red Cloud, that had been built only after hard labor.
4267_287369_000014_000002 But he knew he could accomplish nothing by worrying, and he tried to dismiss the matter from his mind.
4267_287369_000015_000000 They rather expected to see the thing in white again that night, but it did not appear, and morning came without anything having disturbed their heavy sleep, for they were tired from the day's tramp.
4267_287369_000016_000000 It took them the greater part of the day to make a circuit of the base of Phantom Mountain in order to get to a place where a sort of trail led upward.
4267_287369_000017_000000 "It's too late to do anything to night," decided Tom, as they set up the tent.
4267_287369_000017_000001 "We'll rest, and start the first thing in the morning."
4267_287369_000018_000001 "Where are you going, mr Parker?" he asked, as he saw the scientist tramping a little way up the side of the mountain.
4267_287369_000019_000000 "I am going to make some observations," was the answer, and no one paid any more attention to him for some time.
4267_287369_000019_000001 Supper was nearly ready when mr Parker returned.
4267_287369_000019_000002 His face wore a rather serious air, and mr Damon, noting it, asked laughingly:
4267_287369_000020_000000 "Well, did you discover any volcanoes, that may erupt during the night, and scare us to death?"
4267_287369_000021_000000 "No," replied mr Parker, calmly, "but there is every indication that we will soon have a terrific electrical storm.
4267_287369_000021_000001 From a high peak I caught a glimpse of one working this way across the mountains."
4267_287369_000022_000000 "Then we'd better fasten the tent well down," called Tom.
4267_287369_000023_000000 "There will not be much danger from wind," was mr Parker's opinion.
4267_287369_000024_000000 "From what then?" asked mr Jenks.
4267_287369_000025_000000 "From the discharges of lightning among these mountain peaks, which contain so much iron ore.
4267_287369_000026_000000 The fact that the scientist had not always made correct predictions was not now considered by his hearers, and Tom and the two men gazed at mr Parker in some alarm.
4267_287369_000027_000000 "Is there anything we can do to avoid it?" asked mr Jenks.
4267_287369_000028_000001 It will be here in less than half an hour."
4267_287369_000029_000000 "Then we'd better have supper," remarked Tom, practically, "and get ready for it.
4267_287369_000029_000001 Perhaps it may not be as bad as mr Parker fears."
4267_287369_000030_000000 "It will be bad enough," declared the gloomy scientist, and he seemed to find pleasure in his announcement.
4267_287369_000031_000000 The meal was soon over, and Tom busied himself in looking to the guy ropes of the tent, for he feared lest there might be wind with the storm.
4267_287369_000031_000001 That it was coming was evident, for now low mutterings of thunder could be heard off toward the west.
4267_287369_000032_000001 Fitful flashes of lightning could be seen forking across the sky in jagged chains of purple light.
