4267_287369_000040_000001 At times it would be only dimly visible in the blackness, then, suddenly it would stand out in bold relief as a great flash of fire split the clouds.
4267_287369_000041_000000 The thunder, meanwhile, had been growing louder and sharper, indicating the nearer approach of the storm.
4267_287369_000041_000001 Each lightning flash was followed in a second or two, by a terrific clap.
4267_287369_000041_000002 Still there was no wind nor rain, and the campfire burned steadily.
