4830_25898_000005_000000 There never was a prouder mamma than Madam Cluck when she led forth her family of eight downy little chicks.
4830_25898_000005_000003 Old Aunt Cockletop told her that she didn't, and predicted that 'those poor dears would come to bad ends.'
4830_25898_000006_000001 The tragedy began with Chanty, who was the boldest little cockadoodle who ever tried to crow.
4830_25898_000006_000002 Before he had a feather to his bit of a tail, Chanty began to fight, and soon was known as the most quarrelsome chick in the farm yard.
4830_25898_000006_000003 Having pecked his brothers and sisters, he tried to do the same to his playmates, the ducklings, goslings, and young turkeys, and was so disagreeable that all the fowls hated him.
