4830_25904_000012_000000 As a contrast to the wild beasts, I went to see the monkeys, who lived in a fine large house all to themselves.
4830_25904_000012_000001 Here was every variety, from the great ugly chimpanzee to the funny little fellows who played like boys, and cut up all sorts of capers.
4830_25904_000012_000003 He was a cross old party, and sat huddled up in the straw, scowling at every one, like an ill tempered old bachelor.
4830_25904_000012_000005 One poor little chap had lost the curly end of his tail,--I'm afraid the gray one bit it off,--and kept trying to swing like the others, forgetting that the strong, curly end was what he held on with.
4830_25904_000012_000006 He would run up the bare boughs, and give a jump, expecting to catch and swing, but the lame tail wouldn't hold him, and down he'd go, bounce on to the straw.
