5104_33407_000070_000000 "Leif shall sit in the place of honor."
5104_33407_000072_000000 "No man would ever need a cloak there.
5104_33407_000072_000003 The forests are without end.
5104_33407_000072_000004 The sea is full of fish."
5104_33407_000073_000001 They turned and talked to Leif's ship comrades who were scattered among them.
5104_33407_000074_000000 Leif noticed two strangers, an old man who sat at Eric's side and a young woman on the cross bench.
5104_33407_000074_000001 He turned to his brother Thorstein who sat next to him.
5104_33407_000075_000000 "Who are these strangers?" he asked.
5104_33407_000076_000001 "They landed here this spring.
5104_33407_000076_000008 But ill luck came, and he grew poor.
5104_33407_000076_000009 This hurt his pride.
5104_33407_000076_000010 'I will not stay in Iceland and be a beggar,' he said to himself.
