5163_18515_000002_000000 THE ISLAND OF MARKEN
5163_18515_000003_000000 When the boat was nearing the island of Marken, the little yellow cheese had been presented with all due formality to one of the sailors who had been specially kind in the matter of securing good seats for mr King's party, Polly and Phronsie having held a whispered conference in a retired nook, to come out of it bright and smiling.
5163_18515_000004_000001 "It made me happy in the first place because you thought of me, and then, just think, Pet, that poor sailor, how glad he will be to take it home."
5163_18515_000005_000000 "Will he, Polly?" asked Phronsie, in a rapture; "and do you think he has got any little girls?"
5163_18515_000006_000001 And he looks hungry enough."
5163_18515_000008_000000 "Well, maybe he has some; we'll think so, anyway," Polly answered.
5163_18515_000008_000001 "Oh, see, Jasper is calling us."
5163_18515_000010_000000 "They want some stuivers," cried Jasper.
5163_18515_000011_000000 Whiz-spin-went the coins, to fall into the thick stubby grass on the bank.
5163_18515_000011_000002 So Jasper and Polly threw the bits next time in the other direction.
5163_18515_000011_000004 But some one of them always got the money.
5163_18515_000012_000000 "Dear me!
5163_18515_000012_000001 they've eyes just like birds!" exclaimed Parson Henderson; "to think of finding anything in that thick grass."
5163_18515_000013_000000 "Let them alone for that," laughed old mr King; "their wits are sharpened by practice."
5163_18515_000014_000000 "Look out, Phronsie!" exclaimed Jasper.
5163_18515_000014_000001 "Your stuivers went into the water.
5163_18515_000014_000002 Here, I'll hold you up, then you can throw it farther.
5163_18515_000014_000003 There you go," swinging her to his shoulder.
5163_18515_000015_000000 "It did, it did," crowed Phronsie, from her high perch.
5163_18515_000015_000001 "It did, Jasper, go right straight down in the grass just like yours and Polly's."
5163_18515_000016_000000 "So it did, Pet.
5163_18515_000016_000001 Well, now, here is another."
5163_18515_000017_000000 "There's a little girl back there and she hasn't any," mourned Phronsie.
5163_18515_000018_000000 "To be sure," said Jasper.
5163_18515_000018_000001 "Well, we must give her some, and that's a fact." The small girl kept on at a dog trot along the bank, her eyes fixed on the wonderful people who tossed out such magic wealth, and holding out her arms and singing her shrill song.
5163_18515_000018_000002 But when the money was thrown, she was always a bit too late, and the other children, scrambling and scuffling, had pounced upon it, and had made off with it.
5163_18515_000019_000000 "Here, you boys, keep away; you've had enough; we're going to give this to the little girl," Jasper shouted to them as they threw coin after coin.
5163_18515_000020_000000 "They don't know what you are saying, my boy," said old mr King, laughing heartily at the performance, "and they wouldn't mind you in the least if they did."
5163_18515_000021_000000 "I suppose not," said Jasper in chagrin.
5163_18515_000021_000001 "Oh, the mean little beggars!"
5163_18515_000022_000000 "Hold up your apron," screamed Polly to the little girl.
5163_18515_000023_000000 "That's a good idea," said Jasper.
5163_18515_000023_000001 "Why didn't we think of it before?"
5163_18515_000024_000000 "She won't understand any better than the boys," said old mr King. "You forget, children, that these youngsters don't know our language."
5163_18515_000025_000000 "What a bother," exclaimed Jasper, "it is to have so many different languages, anyway!"
5163_18515_000027_000001 And at last the little girl understood by gestures what she could not possibly get into her head by words, so she picked up the skirt of her gown in her sturdy little fists, and one, two, three clinking coins fell safely into it.
5163_18515_000027_000002 But the boys racing along in advance soon discovered this successful trick, and completely swarmed around her, howling dreadfully, so she hastened off, happy in her prize, which she huddled up in her gown as she ran.
5163_18515_000028_000000 "Isn't this just richness?" exclaimed Polly, gazing all about her in an ecstasy.
5163_18515_000028_000001 "Oh, Jasper, what pictures we'll take-and do see that woman's cap! and those pot hooks of hair over her eyes, and that funny, long dangling curl!"
5163_18515_000029_000000 "Take care, Polly, you almost stepped off backward down the bank," warned Adela, pulling her back, as they got off the steamboat and stopped a bit to look around.
5163_18515_000030_000000 "Dear me, did I?" said Polly.
5163_18515_000030_000001 "Well, it's enough to make any one step backward to see such funny clothes; and they are hay making, Adela Gray, as sure as you live."
5163_18515_000031_000000 "Didn't you suppose they would be?" answered Adela, composedly.
5163_18515_000031_000001 "Why, that's one of the things I specially wanted to see."
5163_18515_000032_000000 "Yes, so did I," said Polly.
5163_18515_000032_000001 "Well, it's too, too splendid for anything.
5163_18515_000032_000002 I'm going to begin to take pictures right straight off." Then she stopped and looked at Adela.
5163_18515_000034_000000 "Yes, yes," said Polly, "I'd rather you did first; I truly had, Adela." She ran after her, for Adela had retreated down the bank, and made as if she were going to follow the party.
5163_18515_000034_000001 "Now, Adela, be good and listen to reason."
5163_18515_000036_000000 "Now that's too bad," mourned Polly, "for I'm afraid she'll keep away from me all the while we're on this island, and then I can't get a chance to give her my kodak at all."
5163_18515_000037_000000 "She had it at the 'Model Farm,'" said Jasper, by way of comfort, for Polly's face fell.
5163_18515_000038_000000 "Oh, that was nothing," said Polly, "such a little bit of a while doesn't count."
5163_18515_000039_000000 "Well, let us take pictures as fast as we can," suggested Jasper, "and then when we do come up with Adela, why you'll have yours done."
5163_18515_000041_000000 Jasper looked up.
5163_18515_000041_000001 "There, that's my last picture," he declared.
5163_18515_000041_000002 "At any rate, for now."
5163_18515_000042_000000 "Oh, one more!
5163_18515_000042_000001 I must get a good picture of those girls raking hay." Polly ran off a few steps and sat down on a log to focus.
5163_18515_000042_000002 The Marken girls happened to look up, and immediately whirled around and presented their backs to her.
5163_18515_000045_000000 "Not so good as that," said Polly, sorrowfully.
5163_18515_000045_000001 "Well, it can't be helped." So she was just going to get up from her log, when the girls, thinking from her attitude that she had given up the idea of taking a picture of them, turned back to their work.
5163_18515_000045_000002 As quick as a flash Polly focussed again, and was just touching the button, when a hand came in front of her kodak, and she saw the grinning face of a Marken girl under its pot hook of hair and with the long, dangling curl on one side, close to her own.
5163_18515_000046_000001 "And don't you ever do that again." And the hand was withdrawn, and the girl clattered off as fast as she could run in her wooden shoes.
5163_18515_000047_000000 "I got them," said Polly, running back in triumph to Jasper.
5163_18515_000048_000000 "Yes, and I took a picture of the saucy girl while she was trying to stop yours," said Jasper.
5163_18515_000048_000001 "So she didn't do much harm, after all.
5163_18515_000048_000002 Oh, here is a splendid group!
5163_18515_000048_000003 See them standing by that old tumble down house, Polly," he added excitedly.
5163_18515_000049_000000 "I thought you had taken your last picture, Jasper," said Polly, bursting into a laugh.
5163_18515_000050_000000 "Well, I had then, but I've begun again," said Jasper, recklessly.
5163_18515_000050_000001 He walked up to the group and held out his hand, then pointed to his kodak.
5163_18515_000050_000002 They smiled and nodded, showing all their teeth, and the mother took the littlest baby, for there seemed to be a very generous number of the smaller members of the family, and sat down with it in her lap on the rickety step.
5163_18515_000050_000003 Then they all drew up stiff as sticks, and didn't even wink.
5163_18515_000051_000000 "That's capital," said Jasper, in huge satisfaction, pouring the coins into the mother's lap, where they rolled underneath the fat baby.
5163_18515_000053_000000 "They are her daughter's wedding clothes," said mrs Fisher, "I do believe." For, the old woman was working fearfully hard to make them understand, and pointing first to the white garments and then to the young woman.
5163_18515_000053_000001 "Wedding clothes?" asked mrs Fisher, speaking very slowly.
5163_18515_000055_000000 Polly took the time to study her headgear.
5163_18515_000055_000001 "I think there is a round board under the cap," she confided to Jasper when once out of doors; "how else could they be pulled so tight?
5163_18515_000055_000002 And they look as hard as a drum."
5163_18515_000056_000000 "I didn't investigate," he said, laughing.
5163_18515_000056_000001 "I'll leave that to you, Polly."
5163_18515_000057_000000 "Well, it's funny anyway," she said, "that all the women and girls dress alike in those queer gowns in two parts, and those embroidered jackets over their waists, and those caps and horrible pot hooks and long curls."
