5163_39921_000002_000000 Why mr Cropper Changed His Mind
5163_39921_000003_000000 "Well, Miss Maxwell, how did you get along today?" asked mr Baxter affably, when the new teacher came to the table.
5163_39921_000004_000000 She was a slight, dark girl, rather plain looking, but with a smart, energetic way.
5163_39921_000004_000001 mr Baxter approved of her; he "liked her style," as he would have said.
5163_39921_000005_000000 The summer term had just opened in the Maitland district.
5163_39921_000005_000001 esther Maxwell was a stranger, but she was a capable girl, and had no doubt of her own ability to get and keep the school in good working order. She smiled brightly at mr Baxter.
5163_39921_000006_000000 "Very well for a beginning.
5163_39921_000006_000001 The children seem bright and teachable and not hard to control."
5163_39921_000007_000000 mr Baxter nodded.
5163_39921_000007_000001 "There are no bad children in the school except the Cropper boys-and they can be good enough if they like.
5163_39921_000007_000002 Reckon they weren't there today?"
5163_39921_000009_000001 Forewarned is forearmed, you know.
5163_39921_000009_000002 mr Cropper was opposed to our hiring you.
5163_39921_000009_000003 Not, of course, that he had any personal objection to you, but he is set against female teachers, and when a Cropper is set there is nothing on earth can change him.
5163_39921_000009_000004 He says female teachers can't keep order.
5163_39921_000009_000006 They know he'll back them up in secret, no matter what they do, just to prove his opinions.
5163_39921_000009_000007 Cropper is sly and slippery, and it is hard to corner him."
5163_39921_000010_000000 "Are the boys big?" queried esther anxiously.
5163_39921_000011_000000 "Yes.
5163_39921_000011_000001 Thirteen and fourteen and big for their age.
5163_39921_000011_000003 A man might, but they'd twist you around their fingers.
5163_39921_000011_000004 You'll have your hands full, I'm afraid.
5163_39921_000011_000005 But maybe they'll behave all right after all."
5163_39921_000012_000000 mr Baxter privately had no hope that they would, but esther hoped for the best.
5163_39921_000012_000001 She could not believe that mr Cropper would carry his prejudices into a personal application.
5163_39921_000012_000002 This conviction was strengthened when he overtook her walking from school the next day and drove her home.
5163_39921_000012_000004 He asked interestedly about her school and her work, hoped she was getting on well, and said he had two young rascals of his own to send soon.
5163_39921_000012_000005 esther felt relieved.
5163_39921_000012_000006 She thought that mr Baxter had exaggerated matters a little.
5163_39921_000013_000000 "That plum tree of mrs Charley's is loaded with fruit again this year," remarked mr Baxter at the tea table that evening.
5163_39921_000013_000001 "I came past it today on my way 'cross lots home from the woods.
5163_39921_000013_000002 There will be bushels of plums on it."
5163_39921_000014_000000 "I don't suppose poor mrs Charley will get one of them any more than she ever has," said mrs Baxter indignantly.
5163_39921_000014_000001 "It's a burning shame, that's what it is!
5163_39921_000014_000002 I just wish she could catch the Croppers once."
