5393_19219_000004_000000 CHAPTER two-JEAN VALJEAN STILL WEARS HIS ARM IN A SLING
5393_19219_000005_000000 To realize one's dream.
5393_19219_000005_000001 To whom is this accorded?
5393_19219_000005_000002 There must be elections for this in heaven; we are all candidates, unknown to ourselves; the angels vote.
5393_19219_000005_000003 Cosette and Marius had been elected.
5393_19219_000006_000000 Cosette, both at the mayor's office and at church, was dazzling and touching.
5393_19219_000006_000001 Toussaint, assisted by Nicolette, had dressed her.
5393_19219_000007_000001 It was an exquisite candor expanding and becoming transfigured in the light.
5393_19219_000007_000002 One would have pronounced her a virgin on the point of turning into a goddess.
5393_19219_000009_000001 He took the place of Jean Valjean, who, on account of his arm being still in a sling, could not give his hand to the bride.
5393_19219_000010_000000 Jean Valjean, dressed in black, followed them with a smile.
5393_19219_000011_000000 "Monsieur Fauchelevent," said the grandfather to him, "this is a fine day.
5393_19219_000011_000001 I vote for the end of afflictions and sorrows.
5393_19219_000011_000002 Henceforth, there must be no sadness anywhere.
5393_19219_000011_000003 Pardieu, I decree joy!
5393_19219_000011_000004 Evil has no right to exist.
5393_19219_000011_000005 That there should be any unhappy men is, in sooth, a disgrace to the azure of the sky.
5393_19219_000011_000006 Evil does not come from man, who is good at bottom.
5393_19219_000011_000008 Good, here I am uttering demagogical words!
5393_19219_000011_000009 As far as I am concerned, I have no longer any political opinions; let all me be rich, that is to say, mirthful, and I confine myself to that."
5393_19219_000012_000001 She looked at Marius, she looked at the crowd, she looked at the sky: it seemed as though she feared that she should wake up from her dream.
5393_19219_000012_000002 Her amazed and uneasy air added something indescribably enchanting to her beauty.
5393_19219_000013_000000 "My children," said the grandfather, "here you are, Monsieur le Baron and Madame la Baronne, with an income of thirty thousand livres."
5393_19219_000014_000000 And Cosette, nestling close to Marius, caressed his ear with an angelic whisper: "So it is true.
5393_19219_000014_000001 My name is Marius.
5393_19219_000014_000002 I am Madame Thou."
5393_19219_000015_000000 These two creatures were resplendent.
5393_19219_000015_000002 They realized the verses of Jean Prouvaire; they were forty years old taken together.
5393_19219_000015_000004 They did not see each other, they did not contemplate each other.
5393_19219_000015_000005 Cosette perceived Marius in the midst of a glory; Marius perceived Cosette on an altar.
5393_19219_000015_000006 And on that altar, and in that glory, the two apotheoses mingling, in the background, one knows not how, behind a cloud for Cosette, in a flash for Marius, there was the ideal thing, the real thing, the meeting of the kiss and the dream, the nuptial pillow. All the torments through which they had passed came back to them in intoxication.
5393_19219_000015_000007 It seemed to them that their sorrows, their sleepless nights, their tears, their anguish, their terrors, their despair, converted into caresses and rays of light, rendered still more charming the charming hour which was approaching; and that their griefs were but so many handmaidens who were preparing the toilet of joy.
5393_19219_000015_000008 How good it is to have suffered!
5393_19219_000015_000009 Their unhappiness formed a halo round their happiness. The long agony of their love was terminating in an ascension.
5393_19219_000016_000000 It was the same enchantment in two souls, tinged with voluptuousness in Marius, and with modesty in Cosette.
5393_19219_000017_000000 Such a day is an ineffable mixture of dream and of reality.
5393_19219_000017_000001 One possesses and one supposes.
5393_19219_000017_000002 One still has time before one to divine.
5393_19219_000017_000003 The emotion on that day, of being at mid day and of dreaming of midnight is indescribable.
5393_19219_000017_000004 The delights of these two hearts overflowed upon the crowd, and inspired the passers by with cheerfulness.
5393_19219_000019_000000 Then they returned home to the Rue des Filles du Calvaire.
5393_19219_000019_000001 Marius, triumphant and radiant, mounted side by side with Cosette the staircase up which he had been borne in a dying condition.
5393_19219_000019_000002 The poor, who had trooped to the door, and who shared their purses, blessed them.
5393_19219_000019_000003 There were flowers everywhere.
5393_19219_000019_000004 The house was no less fragrant than the church; after the incense, roses.
5393_19219_000019_000005 They thought they heard voices carolling in the infinite; they had God in their hearts; destiny appeared to them like a ceiling of stars; above their heads they beheld the light of a rising sun
5393_19219_000019_000006 All at once, the clock struck.
5393_19219_000019_000007 Marius glanced at Cosette's charming bare arm, and at the rosy things which were vaguely visible through the lace of her bodice, and Cosette, intercepting Marius' glance, blushed to her very hair.
5393_19219_000020_000000 Quite a number of old family friends of the Gillenormand family had been invited; they pressed about Cosette.
5393_19219_000021_000001 Cosette did not recognize him.
5393_19219_000024_000000 Cosette had never been more tender with Jean Valjean.
5393_19219_000024_000001 She was in unison with Father Gillenormand; while he erected joy into aphorisms and maxims, she exhaled goodness like a perfume.
5393_19219_000024_000002 Happiness desires that all the world should be happy.
5393_19219_000025_000001 She caressed him with her smile.
5393_19219_000026_000000 A banquet had been spread in the dining room.
5393_19219_000027_000000 Illumination as brilliant as the daylight is the necessary seasoning of a great joy.
5393_19219_000027_000001 Mist and obscurity are not accepted by the happy.
5393_19219_000027_000002 They do not consent to be black.
5393_19219_000027_000003 The night, yes; the shadows, no
5393_19219_000027_000004 If there is no sun, one must be made.
5393_19219_000028_000000 The dining room was full of gay things.
5393_19219_000028_000002 The empty spaces between the candelabra were filled in with bouquets, so that where there was not a light, there was a flower.
5393_19219_000029_000000 In the antechamber, three violins and a flute softly played quartettes by Haydn.
5393_19219_000030_000000 Jean Valjean had seated himself on a chair in the drawing room, behind the door, the leaf of which folded back upon him in such a manner as to nearly conceal him.
5393_19219_000030_000001 A few moments before they sat down to table, Cosette came, as though inspired by a sudden whim, and made him a deep courtesy, spreading out her bridal toilet with both hands, and with a tenderly roguish glance, she asked him:
5393_19219_000031_000000 "Father, are you satisfied?"
5393_19219_000032_000000 "Yes," said Jean Valjean, "I am content!"
5393_19219_000033_000000 "Well, then, laugh."
5393_19219_000034_000000 Jean Valjean began to laugh.
5393_19219_000035_000000 A few moments later, Basque announced that dinner was served.
