5393_19219_000043_000001 But, if m Fauchelevent was absent, m Gillenormand was present, and the grandfather beamed for two.
5393_19219_000043_000003 This declaration sufficed.
5393_19219_000043_000004 Moreover, what is an obscure corner in such a submersion of joy?
5393_19219_000043_000005 Cosette and Marius were passing through one of those egotistical and blessed moments when no other faculty is left to a person than that of receiving happiness.
5393_19219_000043_000006 And then, an idea occurred to m Gillenormand.--"Pardieu, this armchair is empty. Come hither, Marius.
5393_19219_000043_000007 Your aunt will permit it, although she has a right to you.
5393_19219_000043_000008 This armchair is for you.
5393_19219_000043_000009 That is legal and delightful. Fortunatus beside Fortunata."--Applause from the whole table.
5393_19219_000043_000010 Marius took Jean Valjean's place beside Cosette, and things fell out so that Cosette, who had, at first, been saddened by Jean Valjean's absence, ended by being satisfied with it.
5393_19219_000043_000011 From the moment when Marius took his place, and was the substitute, Cosette would not have regretted God himself.
5393_19219_000043_000012 She set her sweet little foot, shod in white satin, on Marius' foot.
5393_19219_000044_000000 The arm chair being occupied, m Fauchelevent was obliterated; and nothing was lacking.
5393_19219_000045_000000 And, five minutes afterward, the whole table from one end to the other, was laughing with all the animation of forgetfulness.
5393_19219_000046_000000 At dessert, m Gillenormand, rising to his feet, with a glass of champagne in his hand-only half full so that the palsy of his eighty years might not cause an overflow,--proposed the health of the married pair.
5393_19219_000047_000000 "You shall not escape two sermons," he exclaimed.
5393_19219_000047_000002 Listen to me; I will give you a bit of advice: Adore each other.
5393_19219_000047_000003 I do not make a pack of gyrations, I go straight to the mark, be happy.
5393_19219_000047_000004 In all creation, only the turtle doves are wise.
5393_19219_000047_000005 Philosophers say: 'Moderate your joys.' I say: 'Give rein to your joys.' Be as much smitten with each other as fiends.
5393_19219_000047_000007 The philosophers talk stuff and nonsense.
5393_19219_000047_000008 I should like to stuff their philosophy down their gullets again.
5393_19219_000047_000009 Can there be too many perfumes, too many open rose buds, too many nightingales singing, too many green leaves, too much aurora in life?
5393_19219_000047_000010 can people love each other too much? can people please each other too much?
5393_19219_000047_000011 Take care, Estelle, thou art too pretty!
5393_19219_000047_000012 Have a care, Nemorin, thou art too handsome!
5393_19219_000047_000013 Fine stupidity, in sooth!
5393_19219_000047_000014 Can people enchant each other too much, cajole each other too much, charm each other too much?
5393_19219_000047_000015 Can one be too much alive, too happy? Moderate your joys.
5393_19219_000047_000017 Down with the philosophers!
5393_19219_000047_000018 Wisdom consists in jubilation.
5393_19219_000047_000019 Make merry, let us make merry.
5393_19219_000047_000020 Are we happy because we are good, or are we good because we are happy?
5393_19219_000047_000021 Is the Sancy diamond called the Sancy because it belonged to Harley de Sancy, or because it weighs six hundred carats?
5393_19219_000047_000023 Let us be happy without quibbling and quirking.
5393_19219_000047_000024 Let us obey the sun blindly.
5393_19219_000047_000025 What is the sun?
5393_19219_000047_000026 It is love.
5393_19219_000047_000027 He who says love, says woman.
5393_19219_000047_000029 Ask that demagogue of a Marius if he is not the slave of that little tyrant of a Cosette.
5393_19219_000047_000030 And of his own free will, too, the coward!
5393_19219_000047_000031 Woman!
5393_19219_000047_000032 There is no Robespierre who keeps his place but woman reigns.
