6209_34601_000096_000025 The hurricane is the passage of demons.
6209_34601_000096_000032 My friends, get through the storm as best you can.
6209_34601_000096_000033 I have enough to do to get through life.
6209_34601_000096_000034 Come now, do I keep an inn, or do I not?
6209_34601_000096_000038 I am given up to the voracity of travellers.
6209_34601_000096_000041 I open them and find beggars inside. Is this fair?
6209_34601_000096_000042 Besides, the laws are violated.
6209_34601_000096_000043 Ah! vagabond with your vagabond child!
6209_34601_000096_000044 Mischievous pick pocket, evil minded abortion, so you walk the streets after curfew?
6209_34601_000096_000045 If our good king only knew it, would he not have you thrown into the bottom of a ditch, just to teach you better?
6209_34601_000096_000049 Vagabonds are punished, honest folks who have houses are guarded and protected.
6209_34601_000096_000050 Kings are the fathers of their people.
