6367_74004_000004_000007 He is splendid: big six footer with magnificent muscles, red cheeks, and curly yellow hair.
6367_74004_000004_000010 There was a rumour running at large in the Academy that the Old Fellow wrote poetry, but he ran the mathematics and didn't make such a foozle of it as you might suppose, either.
6367_74004_000006_000000 Sylvia Grant did go down the street, however.
6367_74004_000006_000001 Ruggles, hanging halfway out of the window as usual, saw her, and called me to go and look.
6367_74004_000006_000002 Of course I went.
6367_74004_000006_000003 Sylvia Grant was always worth looking at.
6367_74004_000006_000005 As for brains, that is another thing altogether.
6367_74004_000006_000006 My private opinion is that Sylvia hadn't any, or she would never have preferred-but there, I'm getting on too fast again.
