7059_88364_000001_000000 CHAPTER sixteen
7059_88364_000002_000000 CALIFORNIA AND AMERICA
7059_88364_000003_000000 The moving picture captains of industry, like the California gold finders of eighteen forty nine, making colossal fortunes in two or three years, have the same glorious irresponsibility and occasional need of the sheriff.
7059_88364_000003_000002 Around Los Angeles the greatest and most characteristic moving picture colonies are being built.
7059_88364_000003_000003 Each photoplay magazine has its California letter, telling of the putting up of new studios, and the transfer of actors, with much slap you on the back personal gossip.
7059_88364_000003_000004 This is the outgrowth of the fact that every type of the photoplay but the intimate is founded on some phase of the out of doors.
7059_88364_000003_000005 Being thus dependent, the plant can best be set up where there is no winter.
7059_88364_000003_000006 Besides this, the Los Angeles region has the sea, the mountains, the desert, and many kinds of grove and field. Landscape and architecture are sub tropical.
7059_88364_000003_000007 But for a description of California, ask any traveller or study the background of almost any photoplay.
7059_88364_000004_000000 If the photoplay is the consistent utterance of its scenes, if the actors are incarnations of the land they walk upon, as they should be, California indeed stands a chance to achieve through the films an utterance of her own.
7059_88364_000004_000001 Will this land furthest west be the first to capture the inner spirit of this newest and most curious of the arts?
7059_88364_000004_000002 It certainly has the opportunity that comes with the actors, producers, and equipment.
7059_88364_000004_000003 Let us hope that every region will develop the silent photographic pageant in a local form as outlined in the chapter on Progress and Endowment.
7059_88364_000004_000004 Already the California sort, in the commercial channels, has become the broadly accepted if mediocre national form. People who revere the Pilgrim Fathers of sixteen twenty have often wished those gentlemen had moored their bark in the region of Los Angeles rather than Plymouth Rock, that Boston had been founded there.
7059_88364_000004_000005 At last that landing is achieved.
7059_88364_000005_000000 Patriotic art students have discussed with mingled irony and admiration the Boston domination of the only American culture of the nineteenth century, namely, literature.
7059_88364_000005_000001 Indianapolis has had her day since then, Chicago is lifting her head.
7059_88364_000005_000002 Nevertheless Boston still controls the text book in English and dominates our high schools.
7059_88364_000005_000003 Ironic feelings in this matter on the part of western men are based somewhat on envy and illegitimate cussedness, but are also grounded in the honest hope of a healthful rivalry.
7059_88364_000005_000005 Whatever may be said of the patriarchs, from Oliver Wendell Holmes to amos Bronson Alcott, they were true sons of the New England stone fences and meeting houses.
7059_88364_000005_000006 They could not have been born or nurtured anywhere else on the face of the earth.
7059_88364_000006_000002 Yet there is a difference.
7059_88364_000007_000000 The present day man in the street, man about town Californian has an obvious magnificence about him that is allied to the eucalyptus tree, the pomegranate.
7059_88364_000007_000001 California is a gilded state.
7059_88364_000007_000002 It has not the sordidness of gold, as has Wall Street, but it is the embodiment of the natural ore that the ragged prospector finds.
7059_88364_000007_000003 The gold of California is the color of the orange, the glitter of dawn in the Yosemite, the hue of the golden gate that opens the sunset way to mystic and terrible Cathay and Hindustan.
7059_88364_000008_000001 He declares it is as though it were painted on a Brobdingnagian piece of gilt paper, and he who dampens his finger and thrusts it through finds an alkali valley on the other side, the lonely prickly pear, and a heap of ashes from a deserted camp fire.
7059_88364_000008_000002 He says the citizens of this state lack the richness of an aesthetic and religious tradition.
7059_88364_000008_000003 He says there is no substitute for time.
7059_88364_000008_000004 But even these things make for coincidence.
7059_88364_000008_000007 It is thrillingly possible for the state and the art to acquire spiritual tradition and depth together.
7059_88364_000009_000000 Part of the thinness of California is not only its youth, but the result of the physical fact that the human race is there spread over so many acres of land.
7059_88364_000009_000002 They shout their statistics across the Rockies and the deserts to New York.
7059_88364_000009_000004 His fellow feeling is for the opposite coast line.
7059_88364_000009_000006 Then he tries gestures, and becomes flamboyant, rococo.
7059_88364_000010_000000 These are the defects of the motion picture qualities also.
7059_88364_000010_000002 As an institution it advertises itself with the sweeping gesture.
7059_88364_000010_000003 It has the same passion for coast line.
7059_88364_000010_000005 When, in the hands of masters, they become sources of strength, they will be a different set of virtues from those of New England.
7059_88364_000011_000000 There is no more natural place for the scattering of confetti than this state, except the moving picture scene itself.
7059_88364_000011_000001 Both have a genius for gardens and dancing and carnival.
7059_88364_000012_000004 But the Californian cannot shout "orange blossoms, orange blossoms; heliotrope, heliotrope!" He cannot boom forth "roseleaves, roseleaves" so that he does their beauties justice.
7059_88364_000012_000005 Here is where the photoplay can begin to give him a more delicate utterance.
7059_88364_000012_000006 And he can go on into stranger things and evolve all the Splendor Films into higher types, for the very name of California is splendor.
7059_88364_000012_000007 The California photo playwright can base his Crowd Picture upon the city worshipping mobs of San Francisco.
7059_88364_000012_000008 He can derive his Patriotic and Religious Splendors from something older and more magnificent than the aisles of the Romanesque, namely: the groves of the giant redwoods.
7059_88364_000013_000000 The campaign for a beautiful nation could very well emanate from the west coast, where with the slightest care grow up models for all the world of plant arrangement and tree luxury.
7059_88364_000013_000001 Our mechanical East is reproved, our tension is relaxed, our ugliness is challenged every time we look upon those garden paths and forests.
7059_88364_000014_000000 It is possible for Los Angeles to lay hold of the motion picture as our national text book in Art as Boston appropriated to herself the guardianship of the national text books of Literature.
7059_88364_000014_000002 Edwin Markham, the dean of American singers, Clark Ashton Smith, the young star treader, George Sterling, that son of Ancient Merlin, have in their songs the seeds of better scenarios than California has sent us.
7059_88364_000014_000004 These poems are The Night Sentries and Tidal King of Nations.
7059_88364_000015_000001 Then there is the lovely unforgotten Nora May French and the austere Edward Rowland Sill.
7059_88364_000016_000001 He has invented the new printing.
7067_76047_000001_000000 Section six
7067_76047_000002_000000 After twenty four eventful hours our two students of human motives found themselves together again by the fireplace in the Old George smoking room.
7067_76047_000002_000001 They had resumed their overnight conversation, in a state of considerable tension.
7067_76047_000003_000000 "If you find the accommodation of the car insufficient," said Sir Richmond in a tone of extreme reasonableness, and I admit it is, we can easily hire a larger car in a place like this.
7067_76047_000004_000000 I would not care if you hired an omnibus, said dr Martineau.
7067_76047_000005_000000 "But if you consider it scandalous-and really, Martineau, really!
7067_76047_000006_000000 "Thought is one matter.
7067_76047_000006_000001 Rash, inconsiderate action quite another.
7067_76047_000008_000000 "We might drop Belinda," he suggested turning to his friend and speaking in low, confidential tones.
7067_76047_000008_000001 "She is quite a manageable person.
7067_76047_000008_000002 Quite. She could-for example-be left behind with the luggage and sent on by train.
7067_76047_000009_000001 For a moment he had a wild hope that his companion would agree, and then he perceived that the doctor's silence meant only the preparation of an ultimatum.
7067_76047_000010_000000 "I object to Miss Grammont and that side of the thing, more than I do to Miss Seyffert."
7067_76047_000011_000000 Sir Richmond said nothing.
7067_76047_000012_000000 "It may help you to see this affair from a slightly different angle if I tell you that twice today Miss Seyffert has asked me if you were a married man."
7067_76047_000013_000000 "And of course you told her I was."
7067_76047_000014_000000 "On the second occasion."
7067_76047_000015_000000 Sir Richmond smiled again.
7067_76047_000016_000000 "Frankly," said the doctor, "this adventure is altogether uncongenial to me.
7067_76047_000016_000002 This highway coupling-"
7067_76047_000017_000001 Her manners suggest a person of considerable self control.
7067_76047_000017_000002 And knowing less of me than you do, she probably regards me as almost as safe as-a maiden aunt say.
7067_76047_000017_000003 I'm twice her age.
7067_76047_000017_000004 We are a party of four. There are conventions, there are considerations....
