7190_90543_000079_000000 We had decided that the most likely means of entry was by a window at the end of the hall, and we expected our prey to enter the room by the door.
7190_90543_000079_000002 We were anxious to reproduce the circumstances of the burglary at Sir Joseph Maynard's as nearly as possible, for Quarles declared it was impossible to say what significance there might be in the man's every action.
7190_90543_000080_000001 Nothing happened.
7190_90543_000082_000000 He showed no disappointment, nor any sign that his theory had received a shock.
7190_90543_000083_000000 The next night we were on the watch again, concealed as before.
7190_90543_000084_000000 By arrangement, the house retired to rest early.
7190_90543_000084_000001 So slowly did time go that half the night seemed to have passed when I heard a neighboring church clock strike one, and almost directly afterward the door of the room was opened stealthily and was shut again.
7190_90543_000085_000000 Until that moment I had not heard a sound in the house, and I was not certain that anyone had entered the room even now, until I saw a tiny disk, the end of a ray of light, on the wall.
7190_90543_000085_000002 The next moment he almost trod upon me.
7190_90543_000085_000004 It was discovery from without that he was afraid of.
7190_90543_000085_000005 The ray from his lantern swung about the room for a moment, then he switched on the electric light.
7190_90543_000086_000003 Then he broke off a piece of biscuit, crumbled it in his hands, and scattered the crumbs beside the glasses.
7190_90543_000086_000004 The cigarette box he did not touch, but he took some cigarette ends from his pocket and threw them on the floor.
7190_90543_000086_000005 These preliminaries seemed stereotyped ones, and he appeared glad to be done with them.
7190_90543_000087_000000 There was a curious eagerness in his face as he bent down and opened his bag, taking a thin chisel from it, and from his hip pocket he took a revolver.
7190_90543_000087_000001 His method was systematic.
7190_90543_000087_000003 If a drawer were locked, he pried it open.
7190_90543_000087_000004 He laid the revolver ready to his hand upon the piece of furniture he was examining.
7190_90543_000087_000006 Some of the contents he hardly looked at.
7190_90543_000087_000007 Indeed, most of the contents did not interest him.
7190_90543_000087_000008 But now and then his attention was closer, and at intervals he seemed puzzled, standing quite still, his hands raised, a finger touching his head, almost as a low comedian does when he wishes the audience to realize that he is in deep thought.
7190_90543_000088_000000 For some time I could not make out what kind of article it was to which he gave special attention, but presently noticed that anything in ivory or bone interested him, especially if it were circular.
7190_90543_000088_000001 I remembered the counters in Sir Joseph's room, and wished we had thought to place some in here to see what he would have done with them.
7190_90543_000089_000000 Watching him closely, I was aware that he became more irritable as he proceeded.
7190_90543_000089_000001 One small cabinet, which might possess a secret hiding place, he broke with the chisel, and I noticed that whenever a drawer was locked his scrutiny of the contents was more careful.
7190_90543_000089_000002 He evidently expected that the man he was robbing would value the thing he was looking for, and would be likely to hide it securely.
7190_90543_000090_000000 He had worked round half the room when he suddenly stopped, and, with a quick movement, took up the revolver.
7190_90543_000090_000001 I had not heard a sound in the house, but he had.
7190_90543_000090_000002 There was no sign of doubt in his attitude, which was of a most uncompromising character.
7190_90543_000090_000003 He did not make any movement to switch off the light, he did not attempt to conceal himself.
7190_90543_000090_000004 He just raised his arm and pointed the revolver toward the door, on a level at which the bullet would strike the head of a man of average height.
7190_90543_000091_000000 The handle was turned, and the door began to open.
7190_90543_000091_000001 The next five seconds were full of happenings.
7190_90543_000091_000002 For just a fraction of time I realized that the burglar meant to shoot the intruder without a word of warning, and for a moment I seemed unable to utter a sound.
7190_90543_000091_000003 Then I shouted:
7190_90543_000092_000000 "Back for your life!"
7190_90543_000094_000000 "Quickly, Wigan!" Quarles cried.
7190_90543_000095_000000 I had dashed aside the curtain, and I threw myself upon the burglar just in time to prevent his picking up his weapon with his left hand. He struggled fiercely, and I was glad of Tresman's help in securing him, although the doctor had come perilously near to losing his life by his unexpected intrusion.
7190_90543_000098_000000 "Something in bone or ivory."
7190_90543_000099_000001 "Thank heaven that fool Tresman didn't come sooner!
7190_90543_000099_000002 We might have missed much that was interesting.
7190_90543_000099_000003 You noted how keen he was with every piece of bone he could find, how irritable he was growing.
7190_90543_000099_000004 The counters, Wigan, they were the clew.
7190_90543_000099_000005 But I did not understand their significance at first."
7190_90543_000100_000000 "I do not understand the case now," I confessed, "except that we have caught a mad burglar."
7190_90543_000101_000002 That was my first question, as I told you.
7190_90543_000101_000004 He did, and visited two other doctors.
