7800_283478_000031_000000 "That was as neat a compliment as you ever had paid you, Frank, do you know it?" he asked the other.
7800_283478_000032_000000 Frank smiled, but he did not look displeased.
7800_283478_000033_000000 "I'm glad mr Benchley has such a good opinion of the outdoor chums," he remarked, "for he meant every one of you, as well as me, when he said that.
7800_283478_000034_000000 "That's so," Bluff declared sturdily, "and we've had lots of dandy vacations in the past, too.
7800_283478_000034_000001 What's bothering me is where we ought to go to spend this unexpected time that's been given to us through the fire at the college."
7800_283478_000035_000000 "We'll figure all that out in a day or so, never fear," Will observed.
7800_283478_000036_000000 "Yes," added Jerry, "leave it to Frank, and he'll arrange the details. Chances are we'll be dropping in to see how old Jesse Wilcox is getting on with his muskrat trapping.
7800_283478_000036_000001 I think I'd enjoy another turn up there in the woods."
7800_283478_000037_000001 Just the thought of it gives me a warm feeling around my heart."
7800_283478_000038_000000 "Same here," Bluff told him cheerfully; "I never feel happier than when I smell the woods and get on the trail of game.
7800_283478_000038_000001 That glorious spell we had out on mr Mabie's ranch among the Rockies has haunted me ever since."
7800_283478_000039_000000 They talked it over as they sauntered in the direction of their homes. It happened that Will Milton's house was the first they came to.
7800_283478_000040_000000 "I saw the postman come out of our gate," Will commented.
7800_283478_000040_000001 "I wonder if he brought Uncle Felix the letter he's been expecting for some days. You see, he's got a bad attack of rheumatism; yet he says he must try to get away Down East on some very important business.
7800_283478_000040_000002 Between you and me, he never will be able to do it for days or weeks, he's that doubled up."
7800_283478_000041_000000 "Run in, if you feel like it, Will," Frank told him.
7800_283478_000041_000001 "We'll wait out here for you."
7800_283478_000042_000000 "Yes," added Jerry, as if it might be an afterthought, "and while you're about it, Will, just mention to Uncle Felix that there are four husky boys around, with considerable time to burn just now, and if he wants anybody to take that trip for him we might be coaxed into doing it, if he'd stand for expenses."
7800_283478_000043_000000 At that all of them laughed, as though they considered it a joke.
7800_283478_000043_000001 Will left them shying a few snowballs at a tin can Bluff had set on a fence post.
7800_283478_000045_000000 "Oh, well, I noticed a lot of dodging being done," commented Frank; "and only for that all of us might have made more bull's eyes."
7800_283478_000046_000001 "A hard snowball can sting like fun when it catches you there."
7800_283478_000047_000000 "Yes, look at my right cheek, if you want to prove that," Bluff advised them.
7800_283478_000047_000001 "I got caught there, and it keeps on burning like a hot iron.
7800_283478_000047_000003 They must have fixed up a lot of ammunition that way before they tackled us."
7800_283478_000048_000000 "Seems to me Will's a long time coming out again," complained Jerry. "He's always so much taken up with that photography of his that any old time he's liable to remember something and go to work at it, forgetting all about his chums, who may be kicking their heels in the back yard waiting for him."
7800_283478_000049_000000 "Oh, I don't think he's quite that forgetful!" laughed Frank.
7800_283478_000049_000001 "You know he said Uncle Felix, who loaned us his houseboat to make that trip down the Mississippi to New Orleans, was expecting some important mail to day.
7800_283478_000049_000002 Perhaps he's held Will up to tell him about something. You know Uncle Felix thinks heaps of our chum; yes, and of all the rest of us in the bargain."
7800_283478_000050_000000 "There he comes!" exclaimed Bluff.
7800_283478_000051_000000 "And, say, he seems to be in a terrible hurry," added Jerry, beginning to show a touch of excitement himself.
7800_283478_000051_000001 "Look at him waving his hat over his head?
7800_283478_000051_000002 And do you see how he's grinning from ear to ear?
7800_283478_000051_000003 Now what d'ye reckon can have happened?"
7800_283478_000052_000000 "Oh, Uncle Felix, don't I love you!" muttered Bluff, as if a sudden brilliant idea had come into his mind.
7800_283478_000053_000000 "What's Uncle Felix got to do with it?" demanded Jerry.
7800_283478_000055_000000 Will came hurrying up, and when he spoke his words gave them a thrill.
7800_283492_000001_000000 DID TEDDY KNOW?
7800_283492_000002_000000 "Well, wouldn't that jar you?" remarked Bluff, as he heard what was contained in the brief communication from the lumberman.
7800_283492_000003_000000 "Tried to burn down the camp at Lumber Run, did they?" burst out Jerry.
7800_283492_000003_000001 "Well, if you asked me my opinion, I'd have to admit that I didn't like the looks of a few of those lumberjacks."
7800_283492_000005_000000 "Why, who else would try to turn on mr Darrel that way, and burn his shanties down just when winter is setting in?" asked Bluff.
7800_283492_000006_000000 "We can only give a guess at that," Frank told him.
7800_283492_000007_000001 "After all, I wouldn't put it past him, Frank."
7800_283492_000008_000000 "Who-what-where-how?" demanded Will, apparently confused, and not able to understand what all these strange hints portended.
7800_283492_000009_000000 "We had a specimen of his nasty temper, you know," continued Bluff. "Yes, twice now we've heard him tear around like a bull in a china shop."
7800_283492_000010_000000 "Oh! now I tumble to what you mean," cried Will, who did not often use any sort of slang, and must therefore have been unusually excited to fall into the habit.
7800_283492_000010_000001 "It's Bill-Bill Nackerson!"
7800_283492_000011_000000 Frank nodded his head.
7800_283492_000012_000000 "He's the only party around that we know of who would be mean enough to try to set buildings on fire, just to get even with a man he disliked," he observed.
7800_283492_000014_000000 "That's what we did," asserted Will.
7800_283492_000014_000002 Why, he might have been the death of some of them!"
7800_283492_000015_000000 "Whoever started the fire didn't care a hoot whether it hurt or not, I think," Bluff gave as his opinion.
7800_283492_000016_000000 Frank noticed that the head had disappeared from alongside the open door.
7800_283492_000016_000001 Evidently Teddy had heard enough.
7800_283492_000016_000003 Perhaps he had suspected that the others brought news of some startling character.
7800_283492_000017_000000 Frank did not tell all of his chums about what he had seen.
7800_283492_000017_000001 At the same time it gave him food for much serious thought.
7800_283492_000018_000000 "I wouldn't be at all surprised if Teddy knew something about that fire business," he mentioned to Bluff, a short time later, when they walked together down to the spot where the mink tracks had been seen, as the latter had shown more or less interest in the habits of these little animals.
7800_283492_000020_000000 "He heard strangers talking outside when those two loggers came up," Frank continued, "and even dragged himself to the door to listen.
7800_283492_000020_000001 I saw his head, though after a bit, when we had talked matters over, he went back to the fire again."
7800_283492_000021_000000 "See here, Frank, you don't think Teddy could have set that fire, I hope?" demanded Bluff, uneasily.
7800_283492_000022_000000 "Oh! no, it isn't so bad as that," he was assured.
7800_283492_000023_000000 "The big coward!" muttered Bluff, clenching his fists and shaking his head, as though he would like nothing better than to get in a blow at the bully.
7800_283492_000024_000000 "My opinion, as far as I have any, is about like this," Frank continued.
7800_283492_000024_000001 "After Nackerson struck Teddy the boy happened to overhear him boasting about what he meant to do to the camp at Lumber Run."
7800_283492_000025_000000 "Oh!
7800_283492_000026_000000 "You've got it about straight, Bluff," Frank admitted.
7800_283492_000026_000001 "Of course, I'm only guessing all this, remember.
7800_283492_000027_000000 Bluff was not slow of comprehension.
7800_283492_000027_000001 He saw what Frank's plan was, and while he may not have entirely agreed with such a course, there was no disposition to interfere.
7800_283492_000028_000000 "You know best how to work it, Frank," he said simply.
7800_283492_000028_000001 "I'll keep as mum as an oyster till you give me the tip that it's time to speak. Just as you say, Teddy couldn't have been the one to put the match to the camp over at Lumber Run.
7800_283492_000028_000002 When Nackerson had gone away, perhaps with one of his pals who agreed to stand back of him, that's the time Teddy lit out."
7800_283492_000029_000000 "He struck it pretty hard at first, getting caught in that trap," Frank mused; "but when you come right down to facts I guess it was just as well that it happened to him."
7800_283492_000030_000000 "Huh! that's a queer thing to say," remonstrated Bluff.
7800_283492_000030_000001 "Getting hung up in an old bear trap a blessing in disguise, was it?
7800_283492_000030_000002 I'd like to know how you figure that out, Frank."
7800_283492_000031_000000 "This way," explained the other.
7800_283492_000031_000001 "If he had missed connections with that trap Teddy would have reached the skunk farm only to meet with disappointment."
7800_283492_000032_000000 "Sure he would, because Old Joe, as he called the fur farmer, had pulled up stakes and gone to town for some weeks," Bluff admitted.
7800_283492_000034_000002 We never know when we're well off, do we?
7800_283492_000035_000000 Frank was always accommodating, especially when anything connected with his knowledge of nature was concerned.
7800_283492_000035_000001 He loved to watch the small woods folk when they did not suspect his presence, and learn more and more of their interesting habits.
7800_283492_000036_000000 So that day passed.
7800_283492_000036_000001 Another, and yet a third found the boys enjoying themselves to the limit.
7800_283492_000036_000002 Teddy was showing decided signs of improvement.
7800_283492_000036_000003 He could get around fairly well by now, Jerry having cut him a walking stick, with a crook at the end.
7800_283492_000036_000004 He was beginning to get over the nervousness that had shown itself for a whole day following his advent in the new camp.
7800_283492_000037_000000 Perhaps the boy had feared that Nackerson might come storming along, and insist on his returning to his duties as cook.
7800_283492_000037_000001 He feared the brutal sportsman more than ever, now that he had found such a fine harbor of refuge with the outdoor chums.
7800_283492_000037_000002 To go back to that other drudgery would have been torture.
7800_283492_000038_000000 As soon as he was able to get around he insisted on taking charge of the cooking.
7800_283492_000038_000001 And the boys soon learned that Teddy could manage splendidly.
7800_283492_000038_000002 He had to be shown very little so as to suit their tastes; and none of them regretted in the least that they had extended a helping hand toward one in distress.
7800_283492_000039_000000 A new life was opening up to Teddy.
7800_283492_000039_000001 He had never before come in contact with such an agreeable lot of companions and every hour of the day he tried to prove himself grateful.
7800_283492_000040_000000 Still, he did not mention a word about what he might possibly know of the dastardly deed, when some one attempted to fire the logging camp. Frank often saw a worried expression come over the boy's face, and at such times he suspected that Teddy was puzzling his brain as to just what his duty might be.
7800_283492_000040_000001 He did not like to betray his kinsman, and yet felt that it was not right to refrain from taking someone into his confidence.
7800_283492_000041_000000 "He may speak sooner or later," Frank told himself; "and if he does, it will not be the reward of a hundred dollars for information that will make him tell."
7800_283492_000042_000000 On the second day, about noon, some of the boys were busy near the cabin, laying in an extra supply of firewood.
7800_283492_000042_000001 Frank had an idea they would be visited by a big snowfall before twenty four hours had passed.
7800_283492_000043_000000 "Of course that's only a hazard, fellows," he told Bluff and Jerry, who were helping him add to the handy heap close to the door of the cabin, "but there does seem to be a feeling of dampness in the air, for all it's so cold; and the sun, you notice, shines through a sort of hazy curtain."
7800_283492_000045_000000 "We've got off pretty fortunately so far about storms," Bluff went on, as he threw another armful of fuel on the already huge pile.
7800_283492_000046_000001 That was a lucky shot you made yesterday, Bluff. The buckshot shell did the business, too, for after you fired both barrels the buck went down with a crash."
7800_283492_000048_000000 "If we don't get another while we're up here in the Big Woods," said Jerry, suppressing the natural twinge of jealousy he felt, "we ought to be satisfied with our bag.
7800_283492_000048_000001 And Will is just wild over the bully pictures he's accumulating every day and night."
7800_283492_000049_000000 "It does seem as though he had met with nothing but success, so far," Frank admitted.
7800_283492_000049_000001 "I hope he gets that prize the railroads are offering. So far as I can tell he has a dandy collection already, and we've got some time ahead of us still."
7800_283492_000050_000000 "By the way, where is Will now?" asked Bluff,
7800_283492_000051_000002 I think myself it would be a fine woods picture, and add to his collection."
7800_283492_000052_000000 "Speaking of angels, and you're most sure to hear their wings," chuckled Jerry; "for there's Will coming this way now."
7800_283492_000053_000000 "And on the run, too!" added Frank.
7800_283492_000053_000001 "He looks excited, fellows.
7800_283492_000053_000002 I wonder what he's run across now?"
7800_283492_000054_000000 Will was almost out of breath.
7800_283492_000054_000001 They could see that his face was red from his exertions, but filled with excitement as well; while his eyes were, as Bluff expressed it, "sticking out of his head!"
7800_283492_000055_000000 "Oh! what a whopper!" he gasped, as he drew near the spot where they stood.
7800_283492_000056_000000 "What's that?" demanded Frank, wondering what was coming now.
7800_283492_000058_000000 "Horns, Will?" Bluff fired at him; "cows have horns, deer carry antlers!"
7800_283492_000059_000001 "That's what they were, sticking away up over his head that was like a mule's.
7800_283492_000059_000002 But I snapped him before he turned and trotted off!"
7800_283492_000060_000000 "What trotted off?" shrilled Bluff.
7800_283493_000002_000000 CHAPTER seventeen
7800_283493_000003_000000 THE BIG MOOSE
7800_283493_000004_000000 "A bull moose, you say, Will?" echoed Bluff, his face lighting up with sudden energy.
7800_283493_000005_000001 "I know what you're thinking, Bluff, and that I wouldn't know a bull moose if I saw one.
7800_283493_000005_000002 But you're away off in your guess.
7800_283493_000005_000003 I've so longed to meet up with one when I had my camera with me that I've been picturing how he'd look.
7800_283493_000006_000000 "How did it happen, Will?" asked Frank.
7800_283493_000007_000000 "I was sitting as still as anything," the other related, "after I'd got two dandy snaps at that funny squirrel family playing around the tree where they have their home, and was hoping for another whack at them to complete the set, when all at once I heard a whiffing sound."
7800_283493_000009_000000 "Oh, I looked up to see what had made that queer sound, and there he was, just standing and looking straight at me!
7800_283493_000009_000001 I was nearly scared to death at first, for he looked nearly as big as a barn.
7800_283493_000009_000002 Then I knew it must be a bull moose; and the next thing I found myself taking his picture."
7800_283493_000010_000000 "Did he run away then?" asked Frank.
7800_283493_000011_000000 "Turned and trotted off, as if he didn't care whether school kept or not," Will continued.
7800_283493_000011_000001 "I even had the nerve to shoot him again as he was going.
7800_283493_000011_000002 And don't I hope that first picture turns out good!
7800_283493_000011_000003 It was a remarkable pose, if only the focus was right."
7800_283493_000012_000000 He started toward the cabin door as though anxious to develop his roll of film and discover what success his labor had resulted in.
7800_283493_000012_000001 Bluff caught him by the arm.
7800_283493_000013_000000 "Wait just a minute or two, Will," he pleaded.
7800_283493_000013_000001 "Tell us some more. Where did all this happen?"
7800_283493_000016_000000 "If only you'll hold your horses until I can develop this film, you shall see for yourself whether I know a stag from a bull moose," he was told by the indignant photographer, as the latter broke away and vanished inside the cabin.
7800_283493_000017_000000 Bluff turned to Frank.
7800_283493_000018_000000 "Let's all take a look," he suggested.
7800_283493_000019_000000 "I was just going to say the same myself," Jerry added, being evidently quite as much interested as Bluff.
7800_283493_000020_000000 Frank was more than willing.
7800_283493_000020_000001 He did not feel that they could entirely depend on the evidence of Will, who may have been so startled by the sudden coming of some animal that his imagination worked overtime.
7800_283493_000021_000000 "I hope it wasn't just a mule that strayed away from some lumber camp," he told the others, as they hurried off; but not before Bluff and Jerry had darted inside the cabin and reappeared, carrying their guns.
7800_283493_000023_000000 "Well, chances are it was a bull moose," Frank admitted; "but we'll soon know."
7800_283493_000024_000000 "That light snow falling last night was in our favor, for the tracks will show up well," suggested Jerry.
7800_283493_000025_000000 "Here's the place," Frank told them, a short time afterward.
7800_283493_000026_000000 "Yes, and here's where Will made himself a seat," added Bluff.
7800_283493_000026_000001 "He fixed it so he could sit comfortably, and not have to frighten the family of bushy tails by moving.
7800_283493_000027_000000 "Yes," said Jerry, "which would make it over there that the thing showed up.
7800_283493_000027_000001 Let's take a look at the ground, and see if Will was dreaming or not."
7800_283493_000028_000000 Before half a minute had passed, Frank was pointing to certain marks plainly seen in the inch and more of snow that had fallen on the previous night, perhaps as a sort of forerunner of the coming storm.
7800_283493_000029_000000 "There you are, fellows!" he announced.
7800_283493_000030_000000 All stared hard at the monstrous tracks.
7800_283493_000030_000001 Bluff even got down on hands and knees in order to see better.
7800_283493_000031_000000 "It was a moose, all right, Frank!" said Jerry.
7800_283493_000032_000000 "From the prints made by its big split hoofs, I'm pretty sure of that," Frank asserted; "I'm beginning to believe Will was not so far out of the way, after all, when he said it might be the giant of all Maine moose!"
7800_283493_000033_000000 Bluff got up again, shaking his head.
7800_283493_000034_000000 "Oh, the meanest luck that ever was!" he lamented.
7800_283493_000034_000001 "Why couldn't I have taken a notion to step out here with Will, to watch the way he took the pictures of that squirrel family?
7800_283493_000034_000003 Think how easy I could have dropped him, with such a short distance between.
7800_283493_000034_000004 It's cruel, that's what it is!"
7800_283493_000035_000000 Jerry clapped him on the shoulder.
7800_283493_000037_000000 "You'll have to count me out of that deal," Frank told them.
7800_283493_000037_000001 "You remember that I sprained my ankle yesterday, and a long walk would lay me up.
7800_283493_000037_000002 If anybody goes, it will have to be you two."
7800_283493_000039_000000 "I dare you!" he said.
7800_283493_000040_000000 "No need of that," came the reply, "because I'd be willing to start after that moose alone, and follow him for a week, if I thought I could get a fair crack at him in the end."
7800_283493_000042_000000 They shook hands on the bargain, and so it was ratified.
7800_283493_000044_000000 "The sooner the better, so as to keep his lead cut down as much as we can," he was told by Bluff, after which they both turned toward Frank, for, after all, it would be from this quarter that the signal to start must eventually come.
7800_283493_000045_000000 "No need of rushing off as though you were crazy," Frank told them. "Will says the moose didn't act as though it was badly frightened by seeing him, so it isn't likely it will cover a great many miles before stopping again.
7800_283493_000045_000001 Lunch must be nearly ready.
7800_283493_000045_000002 You must stop long enough to eat a lot, because there's no telling when you may get another square meal."
7800_283493_000046_000000 Bluff glanced quickly at Frank.
7800_283493_000047_000000 "Oh, we won't get lost!" he said loftily.
7800_283493_000048_000000 "I wasn't thinking so much of that as the chance of a blizzard coming down on you," Frank continued.
7800_283493_000048_000001 "Be sure to take along an extra supply of matches.
7800_283493_000048_000002 I'll see to it that each of you has something to help make out a meal or so.
7800_283493_000048_000003 It won't weigh heavy; but if you do need it you'll thank me for it."
7800_283493_000049_000000 Bluff and Jerry may have considered Frank a bit too old womanish, making all that fuss over just going off on a little chase after a wandering moose.
7800_283493_000050_000000 Frank, however, understood what a blizzard meant up there in Maine.
7800_283493_000050_000001 He had been in one or two himself, and would not care to repeat certain experiences that had come his way, unless well provided against hunger and bitter cold.
7800_283493_000051_000000 The three soon reached the cabin.
7800_283493_000051_000002 Will was too busy working at his developing tank to sit down with the rest.
7800_283493_000052_000000 "Plenty of time when I get through with this," he told them.
7800_283493_000052_000001 "Give me five minutes more to get this film in fresh water and then I'll come."
7800_283493_000053_000000 Bluff and Jerry were hurrying as fast as they could.
7800_283493_000053_000001 Frank had redeemed his promise to see that there was something put up in small shape that would help out for supper, in case they were delayed.
7800_283493_000053_000002 He also thrust several small boxes of safety matches into each of their coats, and made sure Bluff had his compass.
7800_283493_000054_000000 "Well," said Will, stepping forward and holding up a dripping film, "take a peep at this, will you, and tell me if I know what I'm talking about or not!"
7800_283493_000055_000000 As soon as the boys saw the splendid negative, in clear cut lights and shadows, they burst into a chorus of cries.
7800_283493_000056_000000 "It's a moose, all right, Will!" Frank told the proud photographer.
7800_283493_000057_000000 "And sure a whopper, just as you said!" added Bluff.
7800_283493_000058_000000 "We take it all back," Jerry vowed.
7800_283493_000058_000001 "After this, we'll own up that you know a bull moose from a mule or a buck deer every time."
7800_283493_000059_000000 "That's going to be a prize picture, all right!"
7800_283493_000060_000000 Those last words from Frank made Will very proud.
7800_283493_000061_000000 "I believe myself that I never got such splendid effects!" he exclaimed.
7800_283493_000061_000001 "Why, I warrant you can see every hair on his head.
7800_283493_000061_000002 Just look how I got him square in the middle of my plate!
7800_283493_000061_000003 It's better to be born lucky than rich, any day."
7800_283493_000062_000000 "I'm done eating," announced Bluff.
7800_283493_000063_000000 "Couldn't cram another bite down, after seeing that picture!" Jerry proclaimed, as he darted over to the corner where his rifle stood, and began to buckle on the webbed belt filled with cartridges.
7800_283493_000065_000000 He hovered about the pair, and constantly warned them against carelessness.
7800_283493_000066_000001 We would feel pretty sorry if anything happened to mar our holiday up here."
7800_283493_000067_000000 "Frank, you can depend on us to be careful," Bluff told him earnestly. "But for goodness' sake don't worry about us.
7800_283493_000067_000001 We're not the 'Babes in the Woods,' you know.
7800_283493_000067_000002 If I do say it myself, we've had our eyeteeth cut for some time.
7800_283493_000067_000003 There never was such a bully chance to get a big moose, and we want to do our level best.
7800_283493_000067_000004 Look for us when we come.
7800_283493_000067_000005 If we don't show up by night, why, chances are we found ourselves so far away that we concluded to make camp."
7800_283493_000068_000000 Bluff and Jerry shook hands gravely all around, even with Teddy.
7800_283493_000069_000000 "Good luck, and I hope you get him!" said that individual, meaning every word, for he had already come to care a great deal for these jolly boys who had been the means of helping him over a very rough place in the road.
7800_283493_000070_000000 "Got everything now?" asked Bluff.
7800_283493_000071_000000 "I should hope so," grunted Jerry.
7800_283493_000071_000001 "We'd be pack horses if we tried to carry any more truck along."
7800_283493_000072_000001 Well, so long, boys, and we all wish you success."
7859_102518_000006_000001 The Persian replied with the threat that he would put the Prophet in chains when he had leisure.
7859_102518_000010_000004 The romans drove the enemy back to the very gates of their camp, but a last charge, headed by the fierce warrior Khaled, broke their firm array when a victory seemed almost assured.
7859_102518_000011_000002 Most of its population were massacred.
7859_102518_000011_000004 He could do nothing; Emesa and Heliopolis were sacked before his eyes, and after an inglorious campaign he hurried to Jerusalem, took the "True Cross" from its sanctuary, where he had replaced it in triumph five years before, and retired to Constantinople.
