8324_286681_000034_000000 "There!" said she.
8324_286682_000001_000000 THE LUCKY MINK
8324_286682_000002_000002 In the winter, when food was not so plentiful and their youngest children were old enough to come with them, they visited there every day.
8324_286682_000002_000003 It was not far from their home.
8324_286682_000003_000001 Then the fathers and mothers were very busy, for in each home there were four or five or six children, hungry and restless, and needing to be taught many things.
8324_286682_000004_000003 When they hunted on land, they could tell by smelling just which way to go for their food.
8324_286682_000005_000001 The fur was darker on their backs than on the under part of their bodies, and their tapering, bushy tails were almost black.
8324_286682_000005_000002 Their under jaws were white, and they were very proud of them.
8324_286682_000005_000003 Perhaps it was because they had so little white fur that they thought so much of it.
8324_286682_000005_000004 You know that is often the way-we think most of those things which are scarce or hard to get.
8324_286682_000006_000000 There was one old Mink by the river who had a white tip on his tail, and that is something which many people have never seen.
8324_286682_000006_000001 It is even more uncommon than for Minks to have white upper lips, and that happens only once in a great while.
8324_286682_000006_000002 This Mink was a bachelor, and nobody knew why. Some people said it was because he was waiting to find a wife with a white tip on her tail, yet that could not have been, for he was too wise to wait for something which might never happen.
8324_286682_000006_000003 However it was he lived alone, and fished and hunted just for himself.
8324_286682_000006_000004 He could dive more quickly, stay under water longer, and hunt by scent better than any other Mink round there.
8324_286682_000006_000005 His fur was sleeker and more shining than that of his friends, and it is no wonder that the sisters of his friends thought that he ought to marry.
8324_286682_000007_000000 When the Minks visited together, somebody was sure to speak of the Bachelor's luck.
8324_286682_000007_000001 They said that, whatever he did, he was always lucky. "It is all because of a white tip on his tail," they said.
8324_286682_000007_000002 "That makes him lucky."
8324_286682_000008_000001 Once the Bachelor heard them wishing this, and he smiled and showed his beautiful teeth, and told them that it was not the tip of his tail but his whole body that made him lucky.
8324_286682_000010_000000 There was a family of young Minks who lived at the foot of the waterfall, where the water splashed and dashed in the way they liked best.
8324_286682_000010_000001 There were four brothers and two sisters in this family, and the brothers were bigger than the sisters (as Mink Brothers always are), although they were all the same age.
8324_286682_000010_000004 He wished to be just like him in every way but one; he did not want to be a bachelor.
8324_286682_000011_000001 Big Brother stood it very patiently for a while; then he snarled at them, and showed his teeth without smiling, and said he would fight anybody who spoke another word about it.
8324_286682_000011_000002 Minks are very brave and very fierce, and never know when to stop if they have begun to fight; so, after that, nobody dared tease Big Brother by saying anything more about the Bachelor.
8324_286682_000011_000003 Sometimes they did look at his tail and smile, but they never spoke, and he pretended not to know what they meant by it.
8324_286682_000012_000000 A few days after this, the Bachelor was caught in a trap-a common, clumsy, wooden trap, put together with nails and twine.
8324_286682_000012_000001 It was not near the river, and none of his friends would have found him, if Big Brother had not happened along.
8324_286682_000012_000002 He could hardly believe what he saw.
8324_286682_000012_000004 He hurried up to where the trap was.
8324_286682_000014_000000 "No," said the Bachelor.
8324_286682_000014_000001 "I can't.
8324_286682_000014_000002 The best way to get out is not to get in-and I've gotten in."
8324_286682_000015_000000 "Can't you do something with your lucky tail to make the trap open?" asked Big Brother.
8324_286682_000016_000000 "I could do something with my teeth," answered the Bachelor, "if they were only where the tip of my tail is.
8324_286682_000016_000001 Why are Minks always walking into traps?" He was trying hard not to be cross, but his eyes showed how he felt, and that was very cross indeed.
8324_286682_000017_000000 Then Big Brother became much excited.
8324_286682_000017_000001 "I have good teeth," said he, "Tell me what to do."
8324_286682_000018_000000 "If you will help me out," said the Bachelor, "I will give you my luck."
8324_286682_000019_000000 "And what shall I do with the tail I have?" asked the young Mink, who thought that the Bachelor was to give him his white tipped tail.
8324_286682_000020_000000 "Never mind now," answered the Bachelor, and he told the young Mink just where to gnaw.
8324_286682_000020_000002 The Bachelor was too brave to groan or make a fuss, when he knew there was anybody around to hear. Big Brother's mouth became very sore, and his stomach became very empty, but still he kept at work.
